Commentary: Anderson starts with a good length delivery outside off, swinging away. Rohit Sharma looks to play at first but makes a leave. That is James Anderson for you.
Back of a length on off, Sharma hops and blocks it out from the crease.
Anderson bowls this one on the pads, Rohit Sharma watches the ball closely and plays it towards deep square leg for a single. India and Rohit Sharma are off the mark.
Length delivery outside off, nipping away from the batter. KL Rahul is smart enough to watch the ball closely and let it go.
Good length delivery outside off, KL Rahul lets it sail through.
On a good length, in the sixth-stump channel. KL Rahul leaves it for the keeper to collect. Good start from James Anderson. Just the one run from it.
Oh, that was a close leave! Good length ball around off, coming back in sharply. Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to that one. The height has saved him there.
Good length ball outside off, an easy leave for Rohit Sharma as he shoulders arms.
Right up there! Mixture of lengths from Robinson as he goes full this time, on off. Rohit Sharma watchfully blocks it out.
Length ball outside off, Sharma watches the ball and lets it sail through.
Well played! Robinson again goes full, on middle, attacking the stumps. Rohit Sharma pushes it towards long off with a very still bat for a brace.
Good length ball on off, angling on. Rohit Sharma tries to defend but misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad. Again the height has saved him there.
Good length delivery outside off, swinging away. KL Rahul leaves it alone. James Anderson has such a good control on that line.
Good length ball, in the fifth-stump channel. KL Rahul lets it be.
An inswinger from Anderson just around off, KL Rahul is surprised by that and looks to block it out. The ball zips past his outside edge.
On a length on off, Rahul defends it on the off side off the back foot.

Good length ball on off, coming back in again. KL Rahul tries to defend it off the front foot but misses. He gets hit on the front pad and Anderson appeals for an LBW. The umpire shakes his head. The impact on that was probably outside off.
On a good length, outside off. KL Rahul is not interested to offer any stroke on that.
Fuller and outside off, Rohit Sharma leaves it untouched.
Great delivery! That came in with the angle around off, Rohit Sharma looks to defend it with a straight bat but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
This is well outside off, Sharma chooses not to play.
A touch fuller on off, Sharma puts a stride forward and blocks it out.
Well played! Length ball outside off, Sharma puts a stride forward and pushes it on the off side.
Robinson serves a length ball well outside off, Sharma shoulders arms. A maiden from Ollie Robinson.
Good length delivery on middle, nipping in. KL Rahul looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. But there is no short leg at the moment.
Length ball outside off, Rahul leans onto it and drives it towards covers for a run.
Fuller length on the pads, Sharma works it off his inner half of the bat towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Length ball around off, Rohit Sharma blocks it out watchfully.
On a length on off, Sharma plays it to point. Both the batters have been very watchful so far.
Length delivery outside off, nipping away. Rohit Sharma could have left it but wants to have a feel of it. He looks to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Rahul gets his bat behind the line of the ball to defend it.
Good length ball, outside off and coming in with the angle. Just straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Rahul's bat.
Good length delivery, on middle. Rahul tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off, swinging away. Sharma shoulders his arms at it.
Length again, outside off and Sharma lets it carry through to the keeper.
Well bowled! A touch fuller, around off. Just straightens after pitching and just beats the outside edge of Rohit Sharma who looks to push at it with a straight bat.
Good length ball, on off. Rahul looks to block with soft hands but edges it towards point. High-quality bowling and high-quality defensive batting. Test cricket at its best.
A touch shorter, on middle and leg. Rahul taps it onto the leg side for one.
Full, on off. Sharma brings out the straight drive but Anderson blocks it with his feet on the follow through.
PEACH! Good length ball, outside off and Sharma leaves it. The ball nips back in sharply after pitching but goes harmlessly past the off stump.
Good length ball, around off and Sharma shoulders his arms at it.
This time Anderson hits the good length hard, outside off. Sharma leaves it and the ball carries through to the keeper.
Robinson pitched it up, outside off and swinging away. Rahul isn't going to offer a stroke to that.
Robinson bowls this one from wide of the crease. The ball pitches outside off and the keeper collects it around leg stump. No shot offered by Rahul.
Length ball, outside off, no swing this time. Rahul isn't interested in playing at that one.
EDGED, JUST SHORT! Length ball, on off and swinging away. Rahul is forced to play at it and he gets the outside edge which falls just short of second slip.
Back-of-a-length delivery, around off. Rahul taps it off the back foot towards backward point.
Good length ball, outside off and swinging away. Rahul leaves it with ease. Maiden over from Ollie Robinson.
Curran starts with a fuller one, on off. Sharma digs it out to point.
Shorter one, on middle and swinging in. Sharma looks to tuck but gets hit on the pads.
BEATEN! Curran pitched it up, on off and the ball holds its line as it goes past the outside edge of Sharma's willow.
Length ball, on middle. Rohit Sharma defends it off the front foot.
A bit fuller, around off. Sharma pushes it towards covers.
Pitched up, around off. Sharma brings out the off-drive but hits it straight to the fielder at mid off. A maiden from Sam Curran.
Full and straight. Rahul hits it to mid on.
Good length ball, outside off. Rahul nudges it with soft hands towards short mid-wicket.
Length ball, on middle. Rahul flicks it to deep square leg for a run.
Length ball, around off. Sharma defends it towards point.
Fuller one, around off and swinging away. Rohit Sharma defends it nicely towards covers.
Length ball, on off and nipping back in. Rohit Sharma works it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On the pads, Rahul works it around the corner for a single.
A touch fuller, on off. Rohit Sharma drives it straight back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, nipping back in. Sharma works it off the inner half of his willow towards square leg. He rotates the strike.
Touch fuller from Curran on leg, Rahul clips it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery, outside off, angling away. Rahul lets it sail through.
Well blocked! Length ball on middle, Rahul keeps his eyes under the ball and blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma leaves it for the keeper to collect.

Good length delivery on off, coming back in. Rohit Sharma looks to defend but the ball swings a long way and hits him on the pads. Anderson appeals for an LBW but nothing from the umpire. Replay shows that it was going over the stumps.
Length delivery on off, Sharma looks to push but misses and gets hit on the body.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma shoulders arms.
On the pads, Sharma looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the pads on the leg side. The batters take a leg bye.
Good length, in the channel outside off. Rahul looks to push it on the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on the pads, Sharma flicks it to square leg.
Length ball on middle, Sharma is solid in his defense.
Good length ball outside off, angling away. Sharma shoulders arms to that one.
Short of a length on off, Sharma taps it in front of the point fielder.

FOUR! First boundary of the day! Curran pitches it full and on the pads, Rohit Sharma flicks it off the wrists towards dep backward square leg for a boundary. Well-controlled shot by Sharma. He moves into double figures as well.
On middle, Sharma defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery around off, Rahul is not interested in playing that.
On a length on middle, angling in. Rahul pushes it towards mid on.
Anderson goes full and on off, KL Rahul clears his front leg and pushes it in between extra cover and mid off. The fielder gives it a chase but it's a long boundary. Three runs are taken.
On a length on off, Sharma watchfully blocks it out.
Length ball on middle, Sharma glances it towards deep square leg for a run.
Good length delivery, in the fifth-stump channel. KL Rahul purposely plays inside the line and leaves.
FOUR! Nicely done! Width on offer outside off, Rohit Sharma latches onto it and steers it through cover-point for a boundary. He has started to feel a bit comfortable now.

FOUR! Edgy! Good length ball on middle, Rohit Sharma looks to work it on the leg side but closes his bat early. The ball goes off the outside edge and past the slip cordon towards third man for a boundary.
Good length delivery outside off, angling away. Rohit Sharma lets it sail through.

FOUR! Third boundary of the over! This time it came off the middle of the bat. Short of a length on off, Rohit Sharma stands tall, opens the face of the bat and punches it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! And more! On the pads, Rohit Sharma tucks it towards the vacant deep square leg region for a boundary. All of a sudden, Rohit Sharma has started to look more comfortable.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma shoulders arms. Excellent over from India's point of view. 16 runs from the over and all came in boundaries.
Anderson pitched it up, outside off and nipping back in. Rahul doesn't offer a shot.
Good length delivery, on off. Rahul plays it with soft hands towards short cover and wants the single, but he's rightly sent back by Sharma.
Length ball, outside off. Rahul shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, pushed wider. No need to play at that.
Full, on off. Rahul drills it to short mid on.
Short ball, outside off. Rahul taps it towards the slip cordon.
Pitched up, around off. Rohit Sharma stays solid in defense.
Length ball on the pads. Sharma tickles it towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Back of a length, on off. Sharma defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Curran strays on the pads again and Rohit Sharma tucks it with ease into the fine leg fence. Sam Curran is leaking boundaries here.
Good length delivery, on off. Sharma taps it to point.
Length ball, around off and played towards mid off by Sharma.
Length ball, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
This time the length ball is pushed wider by Anderson and swings away. Rahul watches it go through to the keeper.
Length again and again it's a fair bit outside off. Rahul isn't going to play at that.
Good length ball, outside off and just nipping back in. Rahul looks to play at it but pulls out of the shot just in time.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul nudges it with soft hands towards the third slip where Jonny Bairstow dives to his right to make a stop.
Fuller delivery, on middle and leg. Rahul looks to flick it through mid-wicket but gets squared up and the ball goes off the leading edge through point. The batsmen get a couple of runs.
Good length delivery, on off. Sharma taps it back onto the deck.
Full, on off and shaping away. Rohit Sharma drives it to mid off.
Pitched up, way outside off with a hint of away movement. Sharma shoulders his arms at that one.
Length ball, straying down the leg side. Sharma looks to flick but misses. Half-hearted appeal from Robinson for caught behind but nothing from the umpire.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone by Rohit Sharma.
Good length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma defends it to point. End of a maiden from Ollie Robinson.
Wood starts off with a good length ball on middle and leg. Rahul blocks it back onto the deck.
Pitched up, around the fifth stump line. Rahul watchfully lets it through to the keeper.
Fuller, outside off, bowled with some venom. Rahul leaves it and the ball hits Buttler's gloves hard as the ball pops out of his gloves.
Length ball, outside off, left alone again by Rahul. Good bounce and carry through to the keeper.
Pitched up, wide outside off. Rahul doesn't play at it.
Length ball, outside off and swinging away. Rahul shoulders his arms at it and Mark Wood starts off with a maiden.
Length ball on the pads, Sharma nicely clips it towards deep square leg for one.
Good length delivery outside off, Rahul is quite happy to leave that alone.

Four byes! Robinson errs in his line and bowls this one way down the leg side, KL Rahul looks to flick but misses. Jos Buttler moves to his left and tries to collect the ball but fails. The ball races away to the fine leg fence. 50 run stand between these two as well.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
On the pads, Rahul looks to nudge it on the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls on the leg side. The batters take a leg bye.
FOUR! On a length on off, Rohit Sharma looks to push it on the off side with soft hands but gets an outside edge. The ball races away to third man for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul lets it sail through.
Short of a length on middle, KL Rahul hops and works it towards leg side for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma is solid in his defense.
Full and well outside off for Rohit Sharma to make a leave.
Length ball on the fifth-stump channel, shaping in. Sharma looks to play at it but pulls it out at the very end moment.
Length ball outside off, Sharma leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Robinson sprays this one down the leg, Rahul misses his flick. Jos Buttler does well to move across and collect the ball.
Down the leg side again, Rahul looks to flick but misses. Jos Buttler moves to his left and stretches his hands out to grab the ball.
A snorter of a delivery around off, Rahul looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length ball on off, KL Rahul gets into the position and punches it through covers to collect a couple of runs.
Length ball on off, Rahul taps it towards point for one.
Touch fuller on off, Sharma clips it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball outside off, Sharma plays it late through backward point. He collects a couple of runs.
Back of a length on off, Sharma rocks back and guides it towards backward point.
FOUR! You cannot bowl short to this guy! Short and on middle, Rohit Sharma pulls it towards the fine leg region for a boundary. He moves onto 47.
Full and on middle, attacking the stumps now. Sharma works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Good length delivery on off, Rahul dabs it to backward point. Rohit Sharma calls for a single but KL Rahul immediately says no.
A short ball on off, KL Rahul is taken aback by that and hops to block that one out.
On the pads, Sharma flicks it towards deep square leg for one.
Robinson bowl a length ball on the pads again, Rahul tucks it towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
A touch fuller on off, Sharma taps it towards backward point.
Good length ball outside off, nicely left by Rohit Sharma.

FIFTY! On the pads again from Robinson, Rohit Sharma flicks it towards mid-wicket for one. He raises his bat and gets acknowledged from the dressing room. He knows that he now has to convert it into three figures. KL Rahul congratulates him as well. This has been a good knock from him so far.
Length ball on middle, Rahul covers the stumps and blocks it out.
BEAUTY! Back of a length, around off and coming in but just straightens after pitching. Sharma gets bamboozled as looks to play inside the line and almost nicks it off.
Pitched up, outside off. Sharma leaves it without any fuss.
Good length ball, around off. Sharma plays it late towards point.
SIX! Short ball, on middle and leg. This one hurried on to Rohit Sharma and he manages to pull it off the top edge over the fine leg boundary. The pace of the delivery carried it way over the ropes.
Length ball, outside off. Sharma doesn't play at it.
Pitched up, outside off and swinging away. Sharma looks to have a dab at it but decides against it in the end.
Length ball, in the channel outside off. Well left by Rahul.
Good length delivery on middle and leg. Rahul tucks it towards square leg.
Full, on off and swinging away. Rahul watchfully gets behind the line of the ball and pushes it back to the bowler.
Pitched up, outside off, this one nips back in sharply. Rahul with another good leave.
Full and straight. Rahul drives it to the left of short mid on but James Anderson makes a good diving stop.
Length ball, outside off, moving away after pitching. Rahul doesn't play at it. No Ball signalled for overstepping.
Good length ball on the stumps. Rahul inside-edges it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! EDGY! 94 mph delivery, on top of off. Rohit looks to tap it to point but gets the inside edge down to the fine leg boundary.
Pitched up, around off. Sharma lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball, wide outside off. No need to play at that one.
FOUR! SLAPPED! 93 mph delivery, short and outside off, just doesn't bounce enough and Rohit Sharma pulls it to the deep mid-wicket fence with authority.
Back of a length, on off, tapped towards covers.
Length ball, around off, nudged towards point by Sharma.
A touch shorter, on middle. Rahul goes back into his crease and nudges it to forward short leg.
Flatter delivery, just outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahul blocks it out.
Floated it up on leg, Rahul works it on the leg side.
Tossed up delivery, on the stumps, blocked out by Rahul.
Flatter delivery, outside off. KL Rahul rocks back and looks to cut it away but misses.
Good length delivery, on the hips. Rohit Sharma works it to deep square leg for one.
Length ball, on the pads. KL Rahul flicks it to deep square leg and gets a single.
A touch shorter, on middle. Sharma nudges it off the back foot towards square leg and rotates the strike.
TWO LEG BYES! Curran strays onto the pads and Rahul misses the flick. The ball goes off the pads and past Buttler towards fine leg. The batsmen get a couple of leg byes.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul defends it off the back foot towards covers.
Full and straight, Rahul drives it nicely but Curran gets a hand to it.
Tossed up on middle, Sharma blocks it out.
Full and on middle, Sharma pushes it to long on for one.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, KL Rahul pushes it towards point. A bit of mix-up there as KL Rahul calls for a single and takes off. Rohit Sharma sends him back and Rahul makes it back to the crease in time.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahul blocks it out.
Flatter and on middle, pushed towards covers.
Full and outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to that one.
On a length on off, Sharma punches it towards covers off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Sharma is solid in his defense.
On the pads, Sharma misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
On a length on middle, Sharma works it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Good length delivery around off, Rahul lets it sail through.
Full and on off, Sharma defends it out watchfully.
Loopy ball on off, pushed towards covers.
FOUR! Up and over! Loopy ball on middle, Rohit Sharma advances down the track and smashes it towards long on for a boundary.
Short and on off, Sharma punches it off the back foot through covers. He gets a couple of runs.
On middle, Sharma eases it down to long on for a run. 100 run stand between Rohit Sharma and KL Rahul. The Indian coaching staff is happy and gives a standing ovation.
Flighted delivery on off, Rahul blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, angling away. Sharma looks to cut it but fails to get any bat to it.
Full and on off, Sharma lunges forward and pushes it towards covers.
On a length on middle, Sharma tucks it towards deep square leg. He calls for the second run and gets it comfortably.
Short ball on middle and leg, Sharma pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball, on off. Rahul punches it off the back foot to the off side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Rahul drives it to short mid on.
Loopy ball on off, Sharma puts a stride forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up on middle, pated back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, Sharma taps it to the off side.
Full and slower through the air on off, Sharma uses his feet and whips it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Loopy ball on middle, driven towards long on for a single.
Length ball, around off and angling away. Left alone by Rahul.
Length ball, on middle. KL Rahul works it through mid-wicket for a run.
Almost chopped on! On a good length, around off. Sharma looks to tap it on the off side but bottom-edges it down to fine leg for a couple. Sharma is very lucky that is missed the stumps.
Length ball, on off. Sharma stays solid in defense.
Good length delivery, outside off. Sharma taps it to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Sharma awkwardly plays it to short mid-wicket.
Flatter one, around off. Rahul cuts it straight to point.
Tossed up on middle. Rahul blocks it well.
Loopy ball, on off, defended to silly point.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery, outside off. Rahul looks to work it on the leg side but gets beaten by the flight and pace of the ball.
Fuller delivery, on off. Rahul squeezes it to backward point.
Tossed up, full and on off. Rahul pushes it down to long on for one.
On a length, around off, tapped to point by Rahul.
Length delivery, outside off and swinging back in. Rahul gets a stride forward and gets it off the inner half of the bat onto his pads.
A touch fuller, on the stumps. Rahul flicks it through mid-wicket and collects a run.
Good length delivery, on top of off. Sharma makes a good leave.
Leg Bye! Fuller delivery, on middle and swinging down leg. Rohit Sharma looks to flick but gets it off the pads to fine leg for a leg bye.
This one is bowled from around the wicket and lands on a perfect length outside off. Straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Rahul's willow.
Flatter and fuller, on off. Well blocked by Rohit Sharma.
Loopy delivery, around off. Sharma drives it to short mid on.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Sharma stays solid in defense.
Flighted again, outside off, not much turn. Sharma watchfully blocks it towards point.
Tossed up, on the stumps. Rohit Sharma clips it to deep mid-wicket and collects a run.
A touch shorter, around off. KL Rahul goes on the back foot and pushes it through covers for a run.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Rahul works it to deep square leg for a single.
Pitched up, outside off. Rohit Sharma drives it straight to the cover region.
A touch shorter, outside off. Sharma looks to tap it on the off side but inside edges it onto his toes.
Good length ball, outside off and well left by Rohit Sharma. The ball swung back in very late and goes just past the off stump.
On a length, outside off. Sharma shoulders his arms at it.

CLOSE! Fuller delivery, on middle and leg and swinging back in sharply. Sharma looks to flick but gets rapped on the pads. There is a huge appeal from Sam Curran but the umpire shakes his head. Probably going down leg.
SIX! SMOKED! Loopy ball on off, KL Rahul shimmies down the track and heaves it over long off for a maximum. He decides to have some fun as well.
Tossed up, full and on off. Rahul blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Rahul defends it to silly point.
Floated it up on middle, Rahul tucks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Rahul hangs back and pushes it towards covers for a single.
Full and on middle, Sharma prods and pushes it to silly mid on.
Length ball on middle, Rahul clips it towards silly mid on and takes off for a quick single. The fielder collects the ball quickly and fires a throw at the bowler's end but misses.
On a length on off, Sharma watchfully blocks it out.
Good length ball on middle, Sharma opens the full face of the bat and pushes it back to Anderson.
Good length delivery in the fifth-stump channel, Sharma leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good length delivery on off, Sharma looks to defend this time as he is forced to play. The ball whizzes past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Outside off, Sharma shoulders arms.
On a length on off, Rahul hops and taps it towards point. He takes off for a quick single and Sharma responds to it well. Excellent running between the wickets.
Good length ball on off, Sharma works it off the outer half of the bat towards point for one.
Length ball on off, Rahul is solid in his defense.
Fuller length on middle, Rahul pushes it through covers for a brace.
Short ball outside off, KL Rahul tries to pull it towards deep square leg but only connects it with thin air around him.
Short ball again, on middle this time. Rahul ducks underneath.
On a length on middle, Sharma tucks it on the leg side.
A touch fuller outside off, Sharma watches the ball closely and lets it go.
Good length ball outside off, swinging in. Sharma keeps his eyes under the ball and looks to block it out but misses. The ball gets past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.

OUT! TIMBER! Of course, it is James Anderson who gets the breakthrough. Good length delivery on off, coming back in sharply. Rohit Sharma puts a stride forward and looks to push it on the off side. He misses the ball completely. The ball skids on, goes through the gate and shatters the stumps. Rohit Sharma could hear the death rattle behind him. He walks back to the pavilion getting applause from the dressing room but he is disappointed. He did all the hard work and now has to depart. End of a fine knock from him. He will have to wait more for his first overseas hundred.
Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara starts his stay at the crease with a leave.
On a length on off, shaping away. Pujara nudges it with soft hands towards backward point. Wicket-maiden for James Anderson.
EDGY! On a length on middle, Rahul looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat early. The ball goes off the outside edge through backward point for a couple of runs.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to that one.
Length ball on off, KL Rahul blocks it out.
FOUR! Runs for Rahul! Width on offer outside off, KL Rahul waits for the ball to come onto him and punches it off the back foot through point for a boundary.
FOUR! STREAKY! Fuller length outside off, KL Rahul puts a stride forward and looks to drive it. The ball goes off the outside edge towards third man for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Rahul lets it sail through.

NOT OUT! Good length on off and nipping back in sharply. Pujara looks to defend but the ball goes through the gate and raps him on the pads. There is a huge appeal from James Anderson and after a lot of thought, Joe Root takes the DRS. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows that the ball was going well over the stumps. England lose their review.
A touch fuller, on off and swinging back in. Pujara pushes it towards covers for a single.
Full and straight, Rahul digs it through mid-wicket and collects three runs.
On a length, outside off. Pujara shoulders his arms at it.
An action replay of the previous delivery as Pujara lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Good length, in the channel around off. Well left by Cheteshwar Pujara.
Length ball, way outside off and left alone by KL Rahul.
Full and straight, pushed back to the bowler.
Wood hits the deck hard on a length on off, coming in with the angle. Rahul taps it towards mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul works it off the inner half of the bat towards deep square leg for one.
Wood bangs this one in short on middle. Pujara jumps on the back foot and defends it well.
On a good length on middle. Pujara nudges it towards mid-wicket and sets off for a quick single.
FOUR! EDGY! Length ball, on off and Pujara dangles his bat at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the second and third slip for a streaky boundary.
Length ball, on off, Pujara strides forward and pushes it to cover.
On a good length, around off. Pujara blocks it well.
Full, outside off, Pujara drives it towards point where the fielder makes a half stop and keeps it to one.
Length ball, on middle. Rahul stays solid in defense.
Back of a length, around off. KL Rahul gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it nicely.
Length ball, sliding down leg. Pujara looks to flick but misses.
On a length, wide outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.
Pitched up, outside off and well left by Cheteshwar Pujara.
An action replay of the previous ball except that there was a hint of away movement this time on.
A touch fuller, bowled in that corridor of uncertainty but Pujara makes an assured leave.
Back of a length, around off. Pujara stays solid in defense. Ollie Robinson begins his new spell with a maiden.
Pitched up, outside off and inviting the drive. KL Rahul does well to leave this one.
Length ball, outside off. Rahul looks to push it on the off side but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Pujara works it off the inner half of his bat to the off side.
Pitched up, outside off, with a hint of away swing. Pujara shoulders his arms at it.
This time it's the big inswinger from Anderson. He bowls this one full and on off. Pujara does well to play it with the swing and past mid on for a couple of runs. 150 up for India.

OUT! CAUGHT! It's James Anderson again with the breakthrough! Length ball, around off and Anderson has already put a seed of doubt in Pujara's mind with that huge inswinger on the previous delivery. Cheteshwar Pujara doesn't know if this one will nip in or move away and he makes the mistake of pushing at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to third slip where Jonny Bairstow takes a nice low catch. Cheteshwar Pujara's dry run at the crease continues.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b James Anderson

Commentary: Good length ball on middle, Rahul looks to work it on the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul lets it sail through.
On a length on off, Rahul lets it go.

Back of a length on off, KL Rahul guides it towards third man. Two fielders give it a chase. One of the fielders does well to push the ball back in and parries it to the covering fielder. Three runs are taken. Fifty up for KL Rahul. He gets appreciated from the dugout and Virat Kohli.
On a length on middle, Kohli tucks it on the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli is not going to offer any stroke at that.
On a length on off, Rahul taps it towards point.
Fuller length on off, Rahul pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on off, Rahul blocks it out.
Good length delivery outside off, KL Rahul lets it sail through. He has no intentions of getting his captain on strike.
FOUR! Fuller length outside off, KL Rahul creams it through cover-point for a boundary. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1.
BEATEN! Robinson starts off with a length ball, from wide of the crease and the ball straightens after pitching. Kohli gets beaten past the outside edge.
Length delivery, on middle. Kohli defends it well.
This one is fuller and pushed wider. Kohli shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, outside off and swinging away. Virat Kohli lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball, on middle. Kohli looks to work it through the on side but gets it off the outer half of the bat towards the bowler.
PEACH! Slightly pitched up, in that corridor of uncertainty and Kohli gets beaten past the outside edge again. Huge appeal from the bowler but the umpire shakes his head and Jos Buttler smiles.
Length ball, outside off and left alone by Rahul.
Pitched up on off, Rahul defends it towards short cover.
FOUR! Length ball, outside off. Rahul waits for it and opens the face of the bat to guide past the slip cordon and into the fence.
Good length delivery, on off and Rahul taps it off the back foot towards point.
Anderson bowls this one on a length, in that corridor of uncertainty. Rahul makes a good leave at the last moment.
Back of a length, on off and swinging back in. Rahul looks to tuck it on the leg side but gets hit in the rib cage.
Full, around off. Kohli squeezes it to point.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Kohli gets off the mark with a flick towards deep square leg. He comes back for the second as well.
Pitched up, around off. Kohli strides forward and defends it to the cover region.
Full, on off, driven nicely to covers.
Length ball, on middle. Kohli works it towards mid-wicket for a run.

Robinson bowls this one from wide of the crease and gets it to nip back in sharply from outside off. Rahul puts a stride forward and inside edges it onto the pads. A half-hearted appeal for an LBW but not given.
Length ball on off, Kohli pushes it towards covers for a run.
Fuller length on middle, Rahul clips it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul leaves it alone.
Nicely bowled! Good length delivery on off, coming back in. Rahul looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
An inswinger on middle, Rahul tucks it towards square leg for one.

What a spell from James Anderson! He bowls his one on a good length on off, Kohli puts a stride forward and looks to defend off the front foot but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.

FOUR! Robinson bowls a short ball on leg, KL Rahul is late on his pull shot. The ball goes off the gloves past the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary. Shouts for 'CATCH IT' but it was very far from Jos Buttler's attempted dive.
On middle, worked towards square leg for a single.
This one is outside off, left alone.
Short of a length on off, Kohli looks to pull but misses.
Full and on off, Kohli pushes it on the leg side.
FOUR BYES! That is poor! No chance for Jos Buttler to grab that. Robinson bowls a length ball way down the leg side. The ball beats everyone and races away to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball on off, Rahul blocks it out.
Full and outside off, swinging away from the batter. Rahul leaves it untouched.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul watches the ball closely and shoulders arms.
Short ball on off, Rahul goes for the pull shot but is hurried onto it. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Stand and admire! Length ball on off, KL Rahul lunges forward, opens the face of the bat and cover-drives it for a boundary. Beautiful batting.
Length ball, on middle. Rahul blocks it out.

Curran starts with a full ball outside off, Virat Kohli reaches out for it and creams it through covers. Dominic Sibley and Haseeb Hameed give it a chase. Both of them slide in pursuit to stop the ball but Dominic Sibley reaches first and puts the ball back inside the ropes. Three runs are taken.
FOUR! Pitched up on off and driven with authority by Rahul. He drives this one beautifully through extra cover and into the fence.
Length again, on off, Rahul drives this one to sweeper cover for one.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Kohli keeps it out to mid-wicket.
Right into the blockhole on middle. Kohli covers the stumps and flicks it towards square leg.
Good length delivery outside off, Kohli again covers the stumps and shoulders his arms.
Good length delivery outside off, Rahul lets it go.
Full and outside off, Rahul lets it sail through.
Fullish and on middle, Rahul pushes it towards mid on for one.
Good length delivery outside off, VK shoulders arms to that.
Outside off, left alone by Kohli.
On a length on middle, Kohli glances it fine leg for a single.
Fullish delivery, way outside off. Kohli leaves it untouched.
Length ball, outside off. Kohli looks to guide it on the off side but the ball keeps low and goes underneath his willow.
Length ball, outside off. Kohli tries to chase this one but the ball goes past the outside edge of his bat.
Good length delivery, around off. Kohli taps it towards point for a single.
Length ball, on top of off. Rahul cuts it from close to his body towards deep point for one.
Curran slightly pitches it up, around off. Kohli stays solid in defense.
Wood bangs this one in at the hips and Rahul does well to tickle it to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Pacey bouncer, outside off and left alone by Rahul.
Back of a length, around off. Rahul jumps on the back foot and punches it through point for one.
Wood goes wide of the crease and hits the pitch hard on a good length outside off. Kohli blocks it with ease.
Length ball, outside off and Kohli leaves it alone.
On a good length, outside off. Kohli gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Full, outside off. Rahul squeezes it out to sweeper cover for a run.
Good length ball, around off. Kohli nudges it with soft hands towards point and collects a run.
The big inswinger from Curran, starts on middle and leg and ends up way outside the leg stump. Jos Buttler dives to his left and collects it well.
Length ball, on off. Rahul plays it with soft hyands to the point region.
Length ball, outside off. This time Rahul looks to push at it but gets beaten.
Fullish delivery on the pads. Rahul works it through square leg for a single.
Wide outside the off stump. Rahul shoulders arms at this one.
Back of a length, around off. Rahul punches it through the covers for a run.
Full and straight, Kohli wrists it through mid-wicket for a couple. 200 is up for India. That shot also brings up the fifty run stand between Kohli and Rahul.
Full, outside off. Kohli drives it towards point and through the hands of the fielder over there. He races back for the second. Good running between the wickets.
Length ball, outside off and left alone by Kohli.
On a length, outside off. Kohli stays solid in defense.
Length ball, coming in from wide outside off. Rahul decides not to play at it.
Curran bangs this one short, around off. Rahul defends it off the back foot.

BEATEN! Length ball, nipping in sharply from outside off. Rahul looks to play at it but the ball goes agonizingly past the outside edge. Huge appeal from the bowler but not given and Joe Root doesn't take the DRS either.
Good length delivery, around off. Rahul pushes it through covers for a single.
Fullish delivery, drifting down leg. Kohli shuffles across looking to flick it but misses.
This one is pushed wider and Kohli shoulders arms at it.
Good length ball on middle, Rahul tucks it towards square leg and gets to the non-striker's end.
Short of a length on off, Kohli sways away from it.
Back of a length on middle, Kohli hops and plays it onto his body.
Short ball on middle, Kohli sits under it.
Mark Wood comes round the wicket. He bowls a good length delivery outside off, angling away. Kohli makes an easy leave.
Short of a length on middle, Kohli defends it down to short leg.
An inswinger from Curran outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
Curran strays this one down the leg side, Rahul looks to flick but misses. Jos Buttler does well to dive to his left and collect the ball.
On a length on off, Rahul dabs it towards backward point.
Full and on the pads, KL Rahul flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Touch fuller on off, Rahul defends it on the off side.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul gets into the line of the ball and tries to defend it. The ball goes past the outside edge into the keeper's mitts.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Kohli.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller length outside off, Virat Kohli sees the width and leans onto that. He carves it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to that.
Full and on off, nipping away. Kohli drives it well but straight to cover.
On the pads, Kohli clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
On a length around off, Rahul watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
Loopy ball on off, Kohli blocks it out.
Floated it up on off, Kohli pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, Kohli works it towards deep square leg for a run.
On off, patted back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Rahul pushes it towards covers for one.
Flighted delivery on off, Kohli taps it on the off side for a run.
Length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good length ball around off, coming back in. Kohli shoulders arms.
Touch fuller on off, Kohli drives it towards extra cover. He rotates the strike by picking up a single.
Robinson angles this one on the pads, Rahul tucks it on the leg side for a single.
Length ball on off, Kohli looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards deep mid-wicket. A single is taken.
On off, Rahul taps it towards covers.
Tossed up, outside off. Kohli blocks it with ease.
FOUR! Loopy ball, very full on off. Kohli hits it back past the bowler and beats mid off for a boundary.
Flatter delivery, on middle. Kohli defends it well.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Kohli pushes it to the cover region.
Flatter delivery, on middle and skidding on. Kohli goes deep in his crease and works it to deep square leg for one.
A touch shorter, on off. Rahul punches it off the back foot towards long on for one.
Length ball, drifting down leg. Rahul looks to flick but misses.

Length ball, outside off and nipping back in sharply. Rahul gets it off the inside edge onto the pads and the ball stops at short cover. The batsmen take a cheeky single as the fielders are still gasping at the almost LBW. KL Rahul moves into the 90s now.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Kohli looks to flick but hits it straight to short leg.
Fuller delivery and again Kohli flicks it to short leg.
Length ball, outside off. Kohli shoulders arms at it.

IN THE AIR...AND SAFE! Length ball, on middle and leg, just bounces a bit extra. Kohli looks to work it on the leg side but gets the edge just past short leg towards mid-wicket. Keeping a short leg fielder almost worked for the hosts.
Flatter delivery, on off. Rahul looks to work it against the spin and gets it off the inner half towards silly mid on.
Tossed up, around off. Rahul pushes it through covers for a run.
A touch short, on middle. Kohli works it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery, on the stumps. Kohli pushes it towards mid on.
Tossed up, full on the stumps. Kohli flicks it straight to square leg.
A touch shorter, around off. Kohli pushes it off the back foot onto the off side.
Good length ball, on middle and leg. Rahul taps it on the leg side.
Wood hits the pitch hard, on a good length and around off. Rahul tries to push at the swinging delivery and inside-edges it onto the pads.
Length ball, on middle. Rahul shuffles across and tucks it to deep square leg for a run.
Nicely bowled! Length from wide of the crease, this one pitches outside off and straightens. Kohli gets beaten past his outside edge.
Length, around off. Kohli plays it to the cover region.
Length again, on off. Kohli opens the face of the bat and nudges it to deep point for one.
Flighted, outside off. Kohli puts out a stride and plays it to long off for a single.
Tossed up, around off and a bit slower. Rahul looks to push at it but gets the inside edge onto the pads. Moeen Ali appeals for an LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
A touch shorter, outside off. Rahul pushes it to cover for one.
Flatter delivery, on middle. Kohli defends it well.
Tossed on, on middle. Kohli nudges it to mid-wicket.
A touch shorter, on off stump. Kohli blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Rahul works it on the off side for one.
Length ball on the pads, Kohli clips it to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Fuller length on off, KL Rahul pushes it with soft hands through covers for a boundary. He moves onto 98.
Short ball on middle, Rahul ducks underneath.
Length ball on off, Rahul blocks it out.
Short again on middle, Rahul is not going to fall for the trap. He sways away from it.
Loopy ball on off, blocked out.
Full and outside off, Kohli drives it towards deep cover for a couple of runs.
Flighted ball on off, Kohli is solid in his defense.
FOUR! Streaky! Loopy ball on off, the ball keeps low. Kohli looks to defend but the ball gets the bottom half of the bat and rolls through Buttler's legs towards third man for a boundary.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up on middle, Kohli nudges it on the leg side.
Fuller and on off, Rahul pushes it towards extra cover.
On a length on off, Rahul watchfully blocks it out.

FOUR! CENTURY! Length ball outside off, KL Rahul cuts it through point and fetches himself a boundary. He is in the zone. Missed out on a hundred at Trent Bridge but he gets it this time and that too at the 'Home of Cricket'. He raises his bat and the Indian dressing room is up on their feet. What a moment for him. An innings to remember for ages.
Short ball on middle, Rahul pulls it towards deep square leg for one.
On off, Kohli pushes it towards covers for one.
Good length ball on off, Rahul blocks it out.
Loopy ball on off, Kohli is solid in his defense.
Slower through the air on off, driven towards deep cover for one.
Tossed up on off, blocked out.
Floated it up on off, Rahul defends it off the front foot.
Full and on off, Rahul pushes it towards deep cover for a single.
On off, defended out.
Back of a length on off, Rahul works it towards backward point for one. That brings up the century stand between Kohli and Rahul. Both of them congratulate each other and give a fist bump.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
On middle, Kohli works it towards the leg side for one.
On a length on off, Rahul guides it towards third man for a single.
Short ball on middle, Kohli ducks under it.
Short of a length on off, Kohli hops and blocks it out from the crease.
Good length delivery on off, Rahul looks to defend but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge. That is the magic of the new ball. Immediately surprises the batsman who is well set.
Lenght ball on middle, Rahul works it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Class written all over it! Robinson bowls a full length ball outside off, overcooked the length a bit. KL Rahul drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Rahul steers it towards covers.
Length ball on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Rahul blocks it out.
Anderson starts with a length ball on off, Kohli watchfully defends it out.
Fuller length on off, Kohli wrists it towards deep square leg for one.
Full again on off, Rahul drives it towards mid off.
Short ball on middle, KL Rahul pulls it towards the fine leg region for a run.
Length ball outside off, a little bit of an away swing there. Kohli taps it on the off side.
Length ball on middle, Kohli defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul leaves it alone.
On a good length on middle, Rahul blocks that out from the crease.
Good length delivery around the fifth-stump channel. Rahul lets it sail through.
Robinson bowls a length ball down the leg side, Rahul looks to tuck it on the leg side but misses.
Touch fuller on off, Rahul plays it to mid on.
Full and well outside off, easy for Rahul to make a leave.
A little bit of hesitation there! Length ball on off, Virat Kohli pushes it towards point. He wants a single but then says no. The fielder there misfields and allows the batters to take a run.
FOUR! Good length delivery on off, KL Rahul punches it off the back foot towards deep point for a boundary.
On a length on off, Rahul guides it to backward point for one.
Good length ball on off, Kohli blocks it out.
Full length ball on off, Kohli pushes it back to the bowler.

Just short! Good length ball around off, nipping away. Virat Kohli looks to defends it off the back foot but gets an outside edge. He played it with soft hands and thus the ball doesn't carry through to the third slip fielder.
On a length outside off, Rahul leaves it alone.
JAFFA! Good length delivery, around off, nipping away. KL Rahul looks to defend but misses. The ball goes past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
On middle, Rahul nudges it to the leg side for a quick single.

OUT! TAKEN! Big big wicket for England! He gets out playing a shot outside off again. Kohli was back amongst the runs but has to depart now. He is disappointed as he walks back to the pavilion. This was on a good length outside off, swinging away from the batter. Virat Kohli could have and should have left it but instead decides to have a poke at it. He sends a flying edge to first slip. Joe Root moves to his right and grabs the catch. He makes no mistake. Ollie Robinson is pumped up, he knows the importance of this wicket.
Howout: c Joe Root b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Length ball, right on the money. Rahane defends it well.
Length ball, on off and Rahane watchfully blocks it out.
Good length ball on middle, Rahul nudges it to mid-wicket for one.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, Rahane flicks it towards deep square leg. He is off the mark with a single.
FOUR! Full length ball outside off, KL Rahul creams it through covers for a boundary.
On off, blocked out.
On a length on middle, Rahul defends it out solidly.
On a length on off, Rahane dabs it to the slip cordon.
Good length ball on middle and leg, coming back in. Some extra bounce on that as well. Rahane looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. Robinson appeals for an LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! Good length delivery on the pads, angling in. Rahane looks to work it on the leg side this time but misses. He gets rapped on the front pad. Ollie Robinson pleads the umpire for an LBW but the umpire says no. Joe Root has a discussion with the teammates and opts for a review at the last second. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows wickets missing as it going down the leg side. England lose another review.
Good length ball, on off. Rahane watchfully blocks it out.
Length ball, on off and coming back in. Rahane defends it off the inner half towards the leg side. A maiden over then, from Ollie Robinson.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul blocks it out.
Length delivery outside off, Rahul shoulders arms.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul slashes it towards deep point for one.
On the pads, Rahane clips it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on middle, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Rahane taps it to point.
Good length ball outside off, seaming away. Rahul lets it sail through.
Short of a length on middle, Rahul tucks it towards square leg for one.
On a length on off, Rahane taps it to point.
Length ball outside off, Rahane looks to defend but gets an outside edge. The ball goes towards the third slip fielder but doesn't carry.
Length delivery around off, Rahane looks to push it on the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.

Good length ball on middle, coming back in. Rahane looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad. Ollie Robinson makes a huge appeal for an LBW but nothing from the umpire. Height might be the issue there.
On middle, worked on the leg side for one.
On a length on middle, Rahane tucks it towards square leg.
Full and on off, Rahane pushes towards covers.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it for the keeper to collect.
On middle, Rahane blocks it out back to the bowler.

Fuller and outside off, Rahane looks to drive but misses. Not really sure why he went for it especially on the last ball of the day. He is lucky to not get an edge there. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Rahul opens his account on Day 2. A gentle delivery, full and around leg, KL flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs.

OUT! Soft dismissal! Massive breakthrough for England very early in the morning. Ollie Robinson bowled a half-volley on the leg stump previously and follows it up with the same length delivery but outside off. KL Rahul is tempted into the cover drive but unfurls it aerially towards the cover fielder. This is one shot KL avoided the whole morning yesterday but sometimes having the runs under your belt make you confident or say overconfident in this case. There was no need to play this shot so early in the day. Dominic Sibley takes an easy catch and that ends a magnificent knock.
Howout: c Dominic Sibley b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Good length ball landing around leg and moving towards middle, Pant defends it from the back foot.
FOUR! Shot! Pant opens his account. Ollie Robinson delivers it very full and around leg, Pant drills his drive past the bowler and down to long on for a boundary.
A length ball on middle and off, Rishabh defends it watchfully from the crease.
Beaten! Fuller in length and outside off, Pant aims for a cover drive but connects only with thin air. A mixed-bag over from Ollie Robinson to start Day 2.

OUT! Rahane is out of here! His miserable form continues. Perfect line, perfect length, it's outside off and there is a little bit of away movement. Rahane is on the front foot, has a needless poke inside the line and edges it to first slip. Joe Root takes the catch easily and India have lost two quick wickets. When you are out of form, you tend to feel the ball and that brought Rahane's demise.
Howout: c Joe Root b James Anderson

Commentary: Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Jadeja tries to flick but misses.
Around off, on a length again, shaping away, Jadeja drops his wrists and allows it through.
Closer to off, a good length delivery, Jadeja taps it down to covers and looks for a run. He is sent back.
Too straight in line, fuller in length, Jadeja works it in front of mid-wicket and gets off the mark with a single.
Anderson lands it on a length and outside off, Pant gets forward and pushes it out with gentle hands to point.
Almost drags it on! Fuller in length and on off, shaping in a bit, Jadeja tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Wrong line, on a good length and down the leg side, Jadeja allows it through to the keeper.

Some miscommunication. Robinson goes probing around off with a full length ball, taking it away with the angle, Jadeja drops it down with soft hands to covers and looks for a run. A bit of a yes-no and eventually they decide not to cross.
A bit edgy! Fuller in length and on off, angling across, Jadeja gets forward to defend and does so with a gentle bottom hand. The soft outside edge rolls to gully.
Back of a length, around off and angling away, Jadeja shoulders arms.
Robinson goes closer to off, a length ball and seaming in, once again Jadeja gets an inside edge as he tries to block. The ball rolls to square leg, RJ wants a run but is sent back.
Oohhh... Pant gives a premeditated charge to Jimmy who lands it on a length and outside off, Pant ends up shouldering his arms.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Good length ball on off, a little bit of movement, Pant defends it from the back foot to the point region.
Pitches it up and around off, Pant covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length and bowled wide outside off, Pant shows no interest in the invitation to drive it away from his body.
Full and just outside off, holding its line, Pant has a push inside the line but only to get beaten. A maiden!
Robinson bowls it full and around leg, Jadeja pushes it down to mid on and lets out a huge shout of no.
Angling away from the left-hander, on a full length around off, Jadeja covers his stumps and lets it be.
Nicely bowled again, that's the angle of Robinson, he is just sliding it across the left-hander to bring the slip cordon into play. So far, Jadeja is watchful in leaving the deliveries outside off.
On a good length and just outside off, it seams back in a bit because of the slope, Jadeja shows good leaving technique.
Good length again, this time on middle and off, Jadeja gets on top of the bounce as he blocks it from the back foot.
Ollie Robinson sticks with his plan of bowling in the corridor around off, Jadeja also sticks with his plan to not play at those deliveries.
Anderson steams in from 'round the wicket and arrows in a length ball on middle and leg, Pant tries to glance but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
In the region outside off, shaping away slightly from a fuller length, Pant shoulders arms.
Fuller again, this one is closer to off, Pant lunges and defends it from the inner portion of his bat.

FOUR! Audacious! Back of a length, outside off, Pant dances down the track, gives himself room and aims to power it over cover-point. However, it's gone off the outside edge to the third man fence. It seems that Anderson sensed the charge and hence shortened his length and tried to bowl wide. Didn't work though.
Good length ball on off, Pant stays back and offers a straight bat in defense.
Pant uses the angle of the bowler, moves back and works a length ball in the gap at mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length and on middle, Pant defends it in front of his pads.
FOUR! Take that! Robinson drags his length short, not short enough to bother the batsman though, Pant rides the bounce and pulls it in front of square leg for a boundary.

FOUR! And again, Pant is in the mood to take on the bowler. Ollie Robinson is again on the shorter side with his length, Rishabh turns in his crease and pulls it once again in front of square leg. This time the connection is not as crisp as the last one but still, it races away to the fence. Advantage of hitting through the slope.
Fuller and on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Ollie Robinson comes from 'round the wicket and bowls it around off, Pant plays it across the line but finds mid on.
A gentle delivery, very much harmless as it's wide outside off, Pant allows it through. 8 from the over, India are four runs away from touching the 300-run mark.
Anderson runs in from over the wicket for Jadeja. Serves a full ball wide outside off, Ravindra shoulders arms.
Fullish and on off, Jadeja plays near his body and defends it to covers. A screaming no from RJ.
Well left! Anderson lands it on a length around middle and off, seaming away, Jadeja sticks back inside the crease and leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, shaping away, Jadeja gets forward to defend but then hides his bat behind his front pad.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Anderson continues to hurl it around off, the ball leaves the batsman with the angle, Jadeja guards his stumps and allows it through.

Pant is on the charge again! He skips down the track to a length ball outside off and tries to smash it over the off side. Fails to get hold of his shot but still manages to clear extra cover. Two taken.
Fuller in length and outside off, Pant has nothing to do with it.
Yet another delivery in the channel outside off, angling away, Pant thinks about pushing inside the line but the ball whizzes past him before his bat can come down.
On a length and close to off, Pant prefers staying on the back foot as he taps it down safely on the off side.
Fuller in length on middle, Pant flicks it gently to mid-wicket. 'Wait in' is the call.
Pitches it up and around off, Pant gets forward and defends it with the angle to the off side.
Anderson serves it full and outside off, angling away, Jadeja lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, around off, Jadeja is on the back foot as he defends it down.
Excellent line, Jimmy continues to keep it on and around off and the angle is taking it away from the batter. Jadeja stays inside the line and keeps his bat away.
Anderson switches to 'round the wicket and angles it into the batter. Outside off, not close enough to make the batsman play.
Anderson stays wide with his line. Serves it full and wide outside off, it's an outswinger, Jadeja decides not to chase.
Beaten! Anderson returns to over the wicket and delivers it on a good length around middle, Jadeja is on the back foot, tries to defend but it whistles past the outside edge.
Wood speeds in from 'round the wicket and angles in a full ball around off, Pant is forward in defense.
Wood goes fuller and on off, at 86 mph, Pant drives but finds the cover fielder.
Oohh...that beats the outside edge by a whisker. Zippy delivery, on a length and outside off, Pant pokes inside the line and misses.
Goes past the edge again! An 87 mph delivery, full and outside off, Rishabh tries driving without any footwork and gets beaten.

Wood clocks 88 mph this time as he delivers it full and on off, Pant plays a mistimed drive to covers where Dominic Sibley makes a tumbling stop. Rishabh practices the flick shot after that, maybe thinking to use the angle and open the leg side region.
Back of a length, outside off and angling in, Pant covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Starts his spell with a length ball on top of off, Jadeja goes on his toes and defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Runs after 18 dot balls. 300 up for India. Curran fails to control his line and serves it down the leg side, Jadeja flicks it behind square leg and sends it racing away to the fence.
Better from Sam Curran. Full and on off, Jadeja defends it close to his body and pushes it towards covers.
Good length ball on off, defended from the back foot to covers.
Very full in length on middle and off, Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler minus any footwork.
Good length ball on off, RJ remains on the back foot and defends it to cover-point. This stand is now worth 20 runs but has gone on for around 46 minutes.
In the channel outside off, on a length, inviting the drive but Rishabh declines the proposal.
Here comes the whip! Wood spears in a fuller length ball on off at 87 mph, Pant uses the angle and wrists it firmly across the line. Finds mid on.
Edgy! Wood lands it on a length and close to off, angling in at 89 mph, Pant tries to defend but it takes the outer edge and rolls to deep point for a single.
Back of a length and around off, jagging back in at 89 mph, Jadeja covers his stumps, trusts the bounces and makes a leave.
On a good length outside off, angling in again at 88 mph, this time it's an easy leave for Jadeja.
Another delivery which has been angled into the batsman, Jadeja stays back-footed and defends it to the leg side.
Curran serves a good length ball, on the pads. Pants stays back and flicks it through square leg for a run.

MISFIELD AND RUNS!  A full length ball, on the pads. Jadeja stays back and tucks it towards mid on. Mark Wood there comes in to collect the ball with a dive but fails to do so cleanly. It rolls in the deep and the batters take two.

EDGY BUT SHORT! A length ball, around off. Jadeja looks to flick it away to the leg side. But the leading edge comes into play and the ball flies towards backward point. Haseeb Hameed moves to his right to collect the ball, but it bounces in front of him and goes past him. The batters take another two.
On a length, around middle and off. Jadeja defends it out solidly.
A full length ball, on middle and leg. Jadeja clips it towards mid on and this time Mark Wood collects it without any hesitation.
Good length ball, outside off. The ball moves away a bit. Jadeja has no stroke to offer here.
FOUR! Pant continues to be on the charge. This was a premeditated shot. A length ball, around off. Pant dances down the track and hammers it through extra cover. The ball races away to the boundary.
A length ball, angling into the pads. Pant flicks it behind square leg. The batters take two. Excellent running!
On the pads again, Pant tucks it in front of square leg and rotates the strike this time with a run.
Short and around middle. Jadeja defends it out watchfully.
Back-of-a-length ball, around off. Jadeja smartly ducks under it.
A length ball, on middle. Jadeja looks to flick it away but the outside edge takes it to the off side. The batters take a quick single.
A touch short and on middle, Jadeja goes back and plays it down to mid-wicket.
Slightly short and outside off, shaping away, Jadeja has nothing to do with it.
Curran makes the batsman play by serving a full ball on off, Jadeja defends it to the off side.
Close to yorker, around off, Jadeja pushes it out to covers.
Jadeja uses the angle of the bowler and flicks it to mid-wicket, finds the fielder.
On a length and around off, angling in, Jadeja stays back and pushes it towards point.
Looped up, around middle. Skidding in from around off. Pant skips down the track and defends it out watchfully.
Tossed up, full and on off. Pant blocks it out solidly.
Floated full and around off. Pant defends it off his front foot.
Flatter and short, around off. Pant goes back and flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Floated and on off. Jadeja pushes it through covers for a single.
Around off, Pant goes back and hits it towards cover-point for another single.
Curran serves a length ball, on off. Pant stays back and smacks it through mid-wicket. The batters cross.
Curran keeps it full this time, around middle. Jadeja clips it towards mid-wicket but straight to the fielder.
A good length ball, around the fourth stump line. Jadeja watches it sail past him to the keeper.
Curran serves it full and around off. Making Jadeja play at it. He defends it to covers solidly.

A full length ball, outside off. The ball nips away a bit. Jadeja prods and looks to defend it out. But the ball takes the outside edge and goes past gully. The batters pick three runs before the fielder cuts it off.
A touch short, around off. Pant rocks back and pulls it behind square leg for a single.
Tossed up ball on middle, pushed back past the diving bowler for a single.

BIG SPIN! Tossed up, around off. The ball lands, grips and spins away big, Jadeja tries to defend but it beats the edge. Buttler fails to collect and the first slip fielder only manages to palm it behind. The batters cross. Ultra Edge confirms there was no edge.
On middle, Pant defends it out solidly.
Floated and on off. Pant blocks it out watchfully.
Slower through the air, too full and on middle, Pant walks forward and knocks it down to long on for a run.
Flatter and shorter on off, punched off the back foot to covers.
Wood serves a full length ball, around off, Pant tries to defend but it takes the outer edge and rolls wide of gully for a couple of runs.
A length ball, going down the leg side. Pant looks to flick it away but misses. Jos Buttler moves to his right and collects the ball safely.
A full length ball, on off. Pant uses the angle and nudges it to mid-wicket. They take a single.
Another full length ball, on the pads this time. Jadeja tucks it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
A length ball, on middle and off. Pant blocks it onto the pitch.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Rishabh Pant falls and the 49-run stand is broken. Mark Wood finally has a wicket to show for his efforts. An 89 mph delivery, a touch short and wide outside off, Pant rocks back to slap it through the line but there is some extra bounce and it collects a thin outside edge on its way to the keeper. Jos Buttler pouches it safely and India lose their sixth wicket, third this morning. The replays, later on, show that the extra pace of Wood brought Pant's downfall. The Indian wicketkeeper-batsman was a shade late with his shot and it possibly took the toe end of his willow.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Mark Wood

Commentary: Floated and on off. Jadeja defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Down the ground! Looped up, full and on off. Jadeja skips down the track and lofts it over mid on. The ball races away to the boundary.
Floated and on middle. Jadeja works it towards long on for a single.
Outside off, Shami prods and defends it out.

OUT! Once again India lose two quick wickets this morning. Moeen flights this one up and lands it full around off, drifting in, Shami decides to flick it across the line but fails to keep his shot down. It's a simple catch for Rory Burns at short mid-wicket and England once again have found a way back. Can they pick the remaining wickets before Lunch?
Howout: c Rory Burns b Moeen Ali

Commentary: Tossed up, full and on middle. Sharma goes back and defends it out.
A length ball, around middle. Jadeja hops and tucks it towards square leg.
Wood serves it on a length, around off. The ball is going away from the left-hander. Jadeja taps it to cover.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Jadeja looks to flick it away but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to the off side.
A short ball, around off, moving away. Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! A length ball, outside off. The ball nips away a bit. Jadeja looks to go after it but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A full length ball, outside off. Jadeja slices it through backward point. They take one and Jadeja keeps the strike.
Floated full and on the pads. Jadeja defends it to the leg side.
Tossed up, full and around off. Jadeja defends it off his front foot to cover-point.
Looped up, full and outside off. The ball turns away sharply. Jadeja leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, Jadeja quietly nudges it to mid-wicket and picks up a single. Two balls for Ishant to survive.
Floated full and on off. Sharma prods and defends it onto the pitch.
Quicker, full and on off. Sharma goes back and defends it out watchfully. Safely done.
A low full toss and outside off. Jadeja taps it onto the ground and the ball meets gully on a bounce.
On a length, around off. Jadeja stays back and defends it towards gully.
Back of a length, around off. Going across the left-hander. Jadeja pushes it through point. He does not take the single.
A length ball, on the bodyline. Jadeja clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Fires in a very full ball on off, Ishant keeps it out safely through point. He looks for a run but Jadeja sends him back.
Well negotiated! Wood goes short and digs it around middle, Ishant walks across and then shoulders arms. There is a leg gully placed in case of any edge.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Jadeja defends it out solidly.
Looped up, on off. Jadeja blocks it out off his front foot.
Floated full and on middle. Jadeja works it through mid-wicket.
Short and on off. Jadeja goes back and punches it through cover-point. They take one.
Floated and on middle. Sharma rocks back and defends it out solidly.
Tossed up and on middle. Sharma defends it out watchfully. He has certainly shown here that he can defend well.
Good length delivery around off, angling away, Jadeja stays on the back foot and defends. The ball rolls in front of gully.
Effort delivery, on a length around middle and off, Jadeja is squared up a bit as he defends it back.
Wood serves a short delivery, wide outside off, Jadeja reaches out and punches it to sweeper cover. Easy two is the call from Jadeja and it's very easy.
A wayward bouncer, down the leg side, Jadeja has nothing to do with it.

FOUR! Jadeja takes on the short delivery this time. It's around leg, Ravindra turns inside the crease and pulls it down to fine leg for a boundary. He has one ball now to take a single and retain strike. Can he?
Nopes, it's a dot ball. Short again from Wood, around middle, Jadeja thinks about pulling but then allows it to go over. That will be all in this session, LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Robinson serves a full length ball, on off. Sharma defends it to the off side solidly.
A full length ball, around off. Sharma blocks this one as well.
A full length ball, around off. Sharma guides it to the left of gully. Rory Burns dives to his left and makes a sharp stop with one hand.

Risky running here! A full length ball, around off. Sharma walks across and defends it to covers. Haseeb Hameed was charging in but still, Sharma called for a single. Jadeja sprints across. Haseeb Hameed collects and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Jadeja gets in safely. Ishant, in fact, wants the second run also and RJ smiles and turns it down.
A length ball, around off. Jadeja stays back and cuts it square on the off side but cannot find the gap.
An appeal for LBW but turned down! A length ball, on the pads. Jadeja looks to flick it away but misses and gets hit on the pads. Robinson makes an appeal but the umpire is not interested.
Anderson returns and delivers a ball outside off, shaping away, Ishant shoulders arms.
Good length ball on off, angling in, Ishant defends it from the crease.

Another risky run. Anderson serves it on a fuller length outside off, Ishant stays back and pushes it towards cover-point. Jadeja calls him through for a quick run as Moeen charges towards the ball. He has a shy at the bowler's end but misses as Ishant dives in.
Sliding down the leg side, Jadeja tries to work it around but fails to middle his shot. It clips his thigh pad and rolls to the right side of the keeper.
Good length delivery on middle and off, Jadeja defends it back from the crease.
Back of a length, around middle and off, Jadeja gives the charge but fails to push it out. The ball takes the inside edge and rolls near the pitch.
Too good for Ishant to even edge that! Full in length and just outside off, straightening off the seam, Ishant gets squared up as he tries to defend. It beats the outside edge very comprehensively.

Well flicked but well stopped as well. Fuller in length and on middle, Ishant walks across and clips it off his pads to square leg. The fielder there dives across to his right and stops the ball. Sharma stays on strike.
Pitches it up and outside off, Sharma is forward as he pushes it with an angled bat to backward point. Haseeb makes a tumbling stop and deflects it towards the slip cordon.
Good length ball on off, angling in, Ishant shuffles across the stumps and plays very late with an angled bat. It runs past gully and Jadeja is ready to take a couple of runs. 350 up for India!
Back of a length, angling down the leg side, Sharma walks across and shoulders arms. Well left.
Good length ball in the line of the stumps, Sharma walks across and tickles it at the final moment to fine leg. No single taken.

Aerial but safe! Back of a length around middle and leg, Jadeja tries to glance it on the leg side but the ball shoots up and takes the shoulder of the bat. It loops in the air and falls just wide of gully.
Shortish and on off, Jadeja stays back and opens the face of his blade to push it out towards point.
Anderson serves a length ball around leg, Jadeja steps back and runs down the track to have a go over the off side but is cramped for room. Only manages to defend it in the end, towards covers.
Movement off the pitch. This one is delivered around middle and leg, shaping away, Jadeja stays back to work it around but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fractionally short and close to off, Jadeja moves back and works it to deep backward square leg for a single. Gets the desired result.
Spears in a very full ball on middle and leg, Ishant stands across in his attempt to flick but it takes a little bit of leading edge and rolls to mid on.
Quite wide outside off, on a good length, Jadeja is not in the mood to chase.
Another delivery in the channel outside off, back of a length, Jadeja isn't flashy at the moment. Lets it be.
Pitches it up and around off, Jadeja is forward and defends it with soft hands to cover-point.
Ollie bowls it on a length around middle and off, Jadeja is very compact in his defense and he does so close to his body.
Excellent stop by Anderson! Back of a length, around leg, Jadeja advances down the track and punches it down the ground, Anderson runs across to his right and makes a diving stop at mid on.
Fires in a very full delivery wide outside off, Jadeja reaches out and digs it out towards covers. Maiden!

Was that gloved? Wood speeds in and digs in a short ball around middle, Ishant shuffles across and then tries to leave the ball. His hands though are very close to the ball and there is some sound too. The ball flies behind, Buttler dives across to his left but fails to hang on. The sound was woody, so maybe a dropped catch.

Direct hit would have consumed Ishant! Back of a length around off, Ishant shuffles and taps it down to the right side of short leg. He looks for a run, Jadeja takes a step forward but then sends back Sharma. Haseeb Hameed has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Sharma was nowhere near the crease.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease in front of short leg.

FOUR! Flashes and flashed hard! Ishant has decided to fight fire with fire. Shortish and around off, Ishant steps back to make room and gives it an almighty thump. It's sliced off the outside half and flies behind backward point for a boundary.
Sliding down the leg side, Ishant walks across and lets it be.
Identical to the last delivery, once again Ishant walks across the stumps and then makes a leave.
MISHIT BUT SAFE! Ollie pitches it up and around off, Jadeja looks for an aerial route, maybe the intention is to go over covers but instead he plays it behind mid off. Two taken.
Angling away from the batsman, on a length, Jadeja strides forward and pushes it defensively to covers.

SAFE! Back of a length, on middle and leg, Jadeja does well to play it with gentle hands in front of square leg. Ishant responds and rushes back for the second run and there is a direct hit at the bowler's end. The umpire refers the decision upstairs and one frame is enough to suggest that Ishant is safely in.
Bouncer and on middle, Jadeja ducks. It's called a no ball.
A length ball around off, angling away, Jadeja drives it through the line but it's not in the gap.

Ishant survives again! Good length ball on middle, Jadeja goes back and taps it down in front of square leg. Jadeja calls his partner through for a quick run and at the same time, Jonny Bairstow attacks the ball. He has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Ishant would have been a goner in case of a direct hit.
Survives! The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Short in length and outside off, played wide of point but turns down the single.
A length delivery, Ravindra Jadeja has just blocked that from his crease.
Gets on the front foot to cover the line and offers a straight bat in defense.
On a length and close to off, Jadeja defends it from the back foot.
Good length ball on middle, it's worked wide of Jonny at mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! Given lbw! Anderson dishes out a length ball outside off and gets it to swerve back in sharply, Ishant is caught on the back foot as he tries to defend. The ball though beats the bat and pings him on the pads. The appeal is made and the finger has gone up. Ishant wants to review it. No bat is involved, shows the Ultra Edge and Ball Tracker shows it to be hitting the stumps. Ishant is gone. A valuable little contribution from the tall man. India are 38 short of the 400-run mark.
Howout: lbw b James Anderson

Commentary: Full in length and close to off, Jadeja presses forward in defense.
Nips away from a length outside off, Jadeja hangs his bat out in defense and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Robinson gets in the line of the stumps, around middle and off, Jadeja plays it late and drops it down with soft hands towards gully.
Short in length and outside off, Jadeja steers it through point for a single.
Full and curling in the air, a big inswinging delivery, Bumrah is forward and defends it to the off side.
Good length ball on off, Bumrah stays back with the intention to defend it on the leg side. But his bat stays outside off and the outside edge takes it all along the ground to gully.
Drifting down the leg side, on back of a length, Jadeja tries to flick but misses.

DROPPED! Short in length and outside off, angling away, Jadeja tries to play late and run it down to possibly third man. But it takes the outside edge and flies quickly to gully. Rory Burns reacts but fails to hang on to the catch. It deflects behind, they take a run. Jadeja wants the second run but then turns quickly. Reaches the crease safely in the end at the bowler's end.
