Another run out opportunity. Fuller in length and on off, swinging in, Bumrah defends it to covers and Jadeja wants to a run. He is sent back and returns with a full length dive as the fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end.
Fuller in length and outside off, shaping away, Bumrah tries to defend but misses.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson has yet another fifer in his illustrious Test career. Mind you, he was a doubtful starter for this Test match but turned up and he has turned up with full force. Serves an outswinger close to the off stump line, Jasprit Bumrah has no other option but to play the line. The ball lands, nips away a shade and kisses the outside edge. An easy take for Jos Buttler and India are now nine down.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Mark Wood comes into the attack and strikes in his first delivery to end the Indian innings. He gets his second wicket of the innings. Wood serves a shortish length ball, around off. Jadeja stays back and looks to heave it away but does not connect well. The ball takes the top edge of the blade and flies high in the air. The ball goes towards mid off. James Anderson settles under it and pouches it comfortably. India are all out for 364.
Howout: c James Anderson b Mark Wood

Commentary: Sharma starts with a length ball, around off. Burns moves across and defends it out solidly.
Sharma serves a length ball, around middle and off. Burns defends it onto the pitch. Looked like he was unaware of the position of the ball after he played it.
A length ball, on off. Burns defends it out solidly.

Did it carry? Oh no, it didn't. Sharma serves a length ball, around off. There is some away movement on the ball. Burns looks to defend it out with an angled bat. The ball though takes the outside edge, it falls just short of Rohit Sharma at second slip. Kohli was ready to celebrate but then he saw Rohit Sharma continued to stay down on the ground, suggesting it didn't carry.
A length ball, on off. Burns defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, around middle and off. Burns taps it down to mid-wicket and takes off for a single. Rory Burns and England are off the mark.
Bumrah starts his spell with a length ball, down the leg side. Burns leaves it alone.
A good length ball, outside off. Coming across the left-hander. Burns watches the ball carefully and shoulders his arms.
Quicker. On a length, outside off. The ball is moving away from the batsman. Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball, outside off. Burns has no stroke to offer this time.
LEG BYE! A full length ball, on the pads. Burns looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and rolls towards fine leg. The batters collect a leg bye.

BEATEN! Jasprit Bumrah with a beauty to end the over! He serves it in the corridor of uncertainty. On a length, just outside off. Sibley looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
Sharma comes 'round the wicket. He serves it on a length, around middle. Burns flicks it towards fine leg. They take one.
Sharma comes over the wicket now for the right-hander. A good length ball, outside off. Sibley shoulders his arms without any hesitation.
A bit of an inswing now. Sharma serves it on a length, around off. The ball comes in. Sibley looks to defend it out but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A length ball, outside off. Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
An inswinger yet again. Full and on off. Sibley defends it out watchfully but off the inner half of his blade.

FOUR! Nice shot! A full length ball, around off, swinging in a bit. Dominic Sibley drives it down the ground by showing the full face of his willow. The ball ends up at the long on fence. This is just amazing from the batsman. Well played.
Now Bumrah comes 'round the wicket. A length ball, outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch. Burns lets it go to the keeper.
On a length, around off. Burns stays inside the crease and defends it out,
Good length ball, outside off. Burns is happy to let that one go to the keeper.
A full length ball, on the pads. Burns clips it to mid-wicket but straight to the fielder.
Good judgement by Rory Burns. Jasprit Bumrah serves a length ball, outside off. The ball nips in a bit. Rory Burns trusts the bounce and shoulders his arms.
A length ball, outside off, an outswinger this time. Left alone by Rory Burns. Another maiden for Bumrah.
Good length ball, outside off, jagging in. Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Sharma serves it on a length, outside off. The ball holds its line after pitching. Sibley has no stroke to offer.
Good length ball, outside off. Sibley has no interest in playing any ball that is pitched away from him.
On a length, outside off, the ball nips in a bit. Sibley shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, around off. Making Sibley play at it. He defends it towards mid on off the inner half of the blade.
A maiden for Ishant Sharma now. A full length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out watchfully.
Bumrah angles in on middle from around off. Burns stays back and keeps it out.
A length ball, on the pads. Burns flicks it to deep square leg. The batters take three before Mohammed Siraj cuts it off near the ropes.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch. Sibley looks to have a poke at it but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
BEATEN AGAIN! A full length ball, just outside the off stump. Sibley is tempted by it and goes for the booming cover drive but misses.
A length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out from the outer half of his bat.
Good length ball, outside off. Sibley shoulders his arms this time. 36 balls done and the English openers have survived the initial phase without much discomfort.
Sharma comes 'round the wicket for the left-hander. A length ball, around off, swinging in. Burns stays back and defends it out to the off side.
FOUR! A loosener and Burns makes the most of it. A length ball, sliding down the leg side. Burns flicks it past Rishabh Pant and the ball ends up going to the boundary at fine leg.
A length ball, around off. Burns stays back and defends it to the off side.
A full length ball, on off. Burns comes forward and blocks it out solidly.

A good length ball, angling in around middle and leg and there is some extra bounce. Burns tries to defend but is squared up. It possibly takes the inside edge and hits him on the thigh pad. The ball falls near the popping crease and stays stationary. Rory though thought it's rolling back and gets ready to kick it away. Meanwhile, he hears a shout of Rory from his partner who wants to steal a run but Burns is too occupied and turns down the proposal.
A full length ball, around off. Burns defends it out to the left of extra cover. Cheteshwar Pujara moves to his left to make the stop.
A full length ball, around leg. Sibley looks to flick it to the on side, but the ball takes the outer half and goes back towards the bowler.
A length ball, on off. Sibley defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Edged but safe! Sibley pushes inside the line from the back foot and edges it behind. It doesn't carry to the slip cordon.
Edged again, safe again. Sibley tries his best to defend a delivery around off, does so with soft hands and the outside edge falls short once more.
The line is too straight and Sibley works it behind square leg for a single.
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, left alone by Burns.
A length delivery outside off, Dominic Sibley makes an easy leave.
Ishant tries to tempt the batsman with a driving length delivery outside off, Sibley is watchful and doesn't want to do anything flashy. Leaves.
Ishant Sharma repeats the last delivery, Dominic Sibley also repeats his last act. Offers no shot.

Movement and bounce. Ishant gets it to tail back in from a length around off, Sibley fails to keep it out and is struck on the pads. We heard the Indians appealing but Ishant himself is not joining them.
Bowls it full and wide outside off, Dominic has nothing to do with it.
Gets closer to the off stump line, fuller in length and shaping in, Sibley is forward as he defends it right under his nose.
Back of a length, around leg and angling away, Rory stays on the back foot and defends it down to the off side.
Bumrah pitches it up around leg, getting it to move away, Burns is opened up a bit in his stance as he defends it from the outer half of his bat to covers.
Fractionally short and around leg, Burns tucks it away but finds the fielder at square leg.
Fuller in length and outside off, angling away, Burns plants his front foot forward to cover his stumps and then makes a leave.
Bumrah continues to probe around leg and it moves towards off, Burns tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the back thigh pad.
This time the line is too straight and the length allows Burns to work it away towards mid-wicket. 10 overs are safely negotiated by the English openers.
Good length delivery but too wide outside off, Sibley has an easy leave.
Close to off, on a length and angling in, Sibley defends it to covers.
Ishant bends his back and delivers it around off, Sibley leans back and sways away.
A touch short and around off, Sibley gets across a bit and plays it down to short mid-wicket.

Back of a length, outside off, Sibley punches it through the gap at backward point. They take a run, want the second but there is hesitation as it's Jadeja attacking the ball. Sibley has taken off, there is a little fumble from Jadeja but Burns is loud and clear in sending his partner back.
Fullish and wide outside off, an outswinger, Burns has the option of driving but he doesn't want to play away from his body.
Straightaway beats the edge with a beauty! Fuller in length and around off, landing on an upright seam and moving away slightly to beat Sibley's defensive bat.
Fuller again, around off, Dominic defends it to the off side, finds covers.
Outswinger from Shami but the line is too wide outside off, allowing Sibley to have an easy leave.
This time Shami has angled a length ball around off, Sibley defends it from the crease.
Plays late. A length ball on off, shaping away a bit, Sibley sticks on the back foot and defends it late with an angled bat.
Fractionally short and outside off, Sibley hangs back and punches it through covers. Doesn't try to hit it hard, just pierces the gap and the slope takes the ball away. Two runs taken.

Play and a miss! Not needed, Rory. Siraj begins with a shortish ball around off, Burns tries to pull but fails to connect. Pant does well to dive across to his right as he stops the ball with one hand.

Aerial but safe! What's Burns trying with Tea around the corner? Fetches a short ball from wide outside off, doesn't middle his shot properly and pops it out away from short mid-wicket. Two runs taken.
Angling away from the batsman, Burns has a tame push inside the line and misses.
Back of a length, around middle and off, Burns goes on the back foot and taps it down defensively to the off side.
Fractionally short again, around middle and leg, Burns turns it behind square leg but finds the fielder.
Shortish and on top of off, Burns defends it off his back foot. Just enough time left for one more over.
Serves a good length delivery, close to off and gets it to shape away, Sibley reads the plan and ignores the delivery.
Shami bowls it on a fuller length around middle, Dominic Sibley flicks it behind square leg for a couple of runs.

Huge shout for a caught behind! Not given. Fractionally short, outside off and curling away, Sibley feels for it and gets beaten. It goes very closely past the edge as Pant collects. The Indians appeal but the umpire stays still. Kohli has a word with his players, Pant is unsure, someone said he heard a noise, Virat thinks and thinks and then decides not to take the DRS.
Sliding down the leg side, tickled to fine leg for a run.
Fuller in length and on off, Burns tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to the off side, Rory looks for a run but Sibley sends him back.
Beaten! Zippy delivery, a touch short and outside off, Burns pokes inside the line and misses. That will be TEA ON DAY 2!
Wrong start, Siraj serves it a bit short but down the leg side, Sibley tries to flick but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! A wicket immediately after Tea, a perfect start for India. Not again, Sibley would say. He has got out in a similar fashion in the last Test match as well. Siraj has not bowled a great delivery, he has just delivered a ball according to his field. On a good length and drifting down the leg side, Sibley clips it aerially to KL Rahul at short mid-wicket who makes no mistake. Mohammed Siraj is running in celebration, India have their first breakthrough.
Howout: c KL Rahul b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: OUT! Two in two, Siraj is on fire! Not a happy return to the Test team for Haseeb. This ball didn't do a lot. Siraj lands it full and around off, it goes on with the angle, pretty straightforward to defend but Hameed is all over the place with his footwork. His front foot lands a little late, his bat is also late in coming down and the ball gets enough time and gap to sneak through to rattle the stumps.
Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Good length ball on off, Root defends it off his back foot.
Root is off the mark! A length ball is angling down the leg side, Joe helps it through square leg and collects a run.
Fuller in length and on off, Burns defends it back. That ends a very dramatic opening over after Tea.
Good length delivery on middle, straightening a bit, Root goes on his back foot and defends it down.
Drops it on a length and serves it outside off, Joe stays back and plays it down defensively to point.
Pitches it up and outside off, Root presses forward and pushes it with an angled bat to point.
A hint of away movement as it lands on a length outside off, Root has nothing to do with it.
Fractionally short and wide outside off, Root tries to steer it past point but finds Jadeja.
Good length delivery outside off, this time Root tries to run it down to third man but KL Rahul dives full length to his right from third slip to stop the racing ball. Well done, a maiden completed.
Siraj angles across a length ball outside off, Burns covers his stumps and allows it through to the keeper.
Full in length and on off, Rory defends it back off the front foot.
A length delivery close to off, Burns remains hanging on the back leg as he brings his bat down in defense.
Short in length and outside off, shaping away, Burns has things under control as he guards his stumps and shoulders arms.
Siraj comes from 'round the wicket and delivers it on a length and outside off, Burns allows it through.
Beaten all ends up! Siraj angles in a fuller length ball close to off, Rory tries to play the line, offers a dead bat but it nips away to beat the outside edge.
Shortish and on off, Root punches it from the back foot but finds the point fielder.
A gentle outswinger, outside off, Root has an easy leave.
Slightly short and around off, it's bowled from wide of the crease, Root is on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Presses forward to a length ball and pushes it with gentle hands to point. Finds Jadeja again.
FOUR! Put away in style! Fuller in length and drifting down the leg side, Root picks it up off his pads and flicks it with beautiful timing through square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it from the back foot to covers.
A length delivery outside off, from 'round the wicket, Rory leaves.
Outside off, left alone.
A touch short and outside off, holding its line, Burns watches it closely before leaving it.
Full in length and around off, curling into the batsman, Burns is forward as he defends it back. Siraj picks up the ball and mimes a throw at the striker.
Fuller in length and around off, Rory pushes it to the left of cover-point. The fielder there slides to stop the ball.
Siraj returns to over the wicket and digs in a bouncer, Burns ducks and Pant jumps to collect the ball.

A muted appeal from the bowler. Shami hurls in a length ball on middle and leg, Root tries to work it around but misses. It goes off his pads to square leg and they cross. The umpire takes his time before signalling for a leg bye. Was just waiting to see if India want to review it. Going down and possibly too high as well.
Fuller in length and outside off, left alone.
On a length and just outside off, shaping in, Burns tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A length delivery outside off, angling in, Burns covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Shami serves it on a length and outside off, holding its line, Rory has nothing to do with it.
Another gentle delivery in the channel outside off, Rory makes another leave to cap off the 20th over.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Full in length and going down the leg side, Root deflects it neatly down to fine leg for a boundary.
This one is on middle and leg, a length ball, Root works it off his pads but finds square leg.
Yet another full delivery is going down the leg side, Joe tickles it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, around off and angling away, Rory plays inside the line and gets beaten.
Shortish and on middle, Burns helps it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

MISSING THE STUMPS! India lose a review. Siraj gets a length ball to land around off as it moves back into the batsman, Root tries to defend but misses and is thudded on the pads. The bowler appeals but the umpire shows no interest. Siraj is convinced, Kohli wants to take the second opinion of the keeper but Pant isn't looking too convinced. Virat has a call to make and he eventually gives in. Takes the DRS but the Ball Tracker finds it to be missing the leg stump.
Short and wide outside off, Burns rocks back to cut but gets a bottom edge.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Fuller in length and on off, defended to the off side.
FOUR! Well played! Short in length and outside off, Burns hangs back, plays at it late and runs it down to third man for a boundary.
Angles in a fuller length ball on off, Rory defends it off his front foot.
A big outswinger, on a length and outside off, Burns strides forward to cover the line and then lets it be.
A hint of inward movement there, from around middle and leg, Root tries to flick but it takes the pads and rolls to square leg.
Angling in from around off, Root is behind the line as he defends it from the back foot.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, drifting down, Root tries to flick but misses. Once again it goes off his pads to square leg. Abhimanyu Easwaran (sub) misfields but no run conceded.

SAFE AGAIN! India have wasted two reviews. Siraj delivers it on off, gets it to jag back into the batsman, Root is unable to defend and is pinged on the front pad. A huge appeal for an lbw, again the umpire is not interested. Virat Kohli joins the conference with Rishabh Pant and Mohammed Siraj. Again both the keeper and the bowler are not on the same page. Kohli is having a big laugh as he eventually signals for the DRS. Nothing to laugh about now, the ball is missing the leg stump as shown by the Ball Tracker. India have burnt two reviews.
On a length and around off, played late from the back foot to backward point.
Fuller in length and on off, Root defends it down towards mid on.
Starts from 'round the wicket and bowls it on a fuller length outside off, Burns shoulders arms.
In the channel outside off, straightening off the seam, Burns allows it through to the keeper.
Uppish but safe! Full and around middle, angling in, Burns flicks it a bit aerially but it doesn't carry to square leg. The fielder there is lazy in going down and misfields. Two runs taken.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller in length and outside off, Burns tries to drive but plays outside the line. Is beaten on the inside edge.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Rory defends it from the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it safely from the back foot.
Yet another back foot defense offered by Joe Root.
Siraj pitches it up and outside off, Root is forward to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Some movement off the seam. On a length and around off, Root sticks on the back foot and defends it down.
Siraj goes fuller and around off, nipping in, Joe is forward to defend but again gets an inside edge. It rolls to short mid-wicket.
A length ball on middle, Root gets behind the line and blocks it from the inside part of his bat to mid-wicket.
Good length ball close to off, angling in and straightening, Burns sits on the back foot and taps it down to gully.
Identical to the last delivery, this time Rory offers no shot.
Sharma pitches it further up and keeps it close to off, Burns defends it with gentle hands to the off side.
Ishant gets even more closer to off stump, fuller in length and Burns gets the chance to flick it wide of mid on. A single is collected.
Ishant lets out a tempter for Root, it's on a driving length but too wide outside off to lure the batsman.
A length delivery on off, jagging back in sharply, Root has a straight bat in front of his pads as he blocks.
Siraj delivers a length ball around middle, moving away, Burns covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Good length and close to off, angling away, Rory lets it through to the keeper.

FOUR! Well played! Siraj is a little too full around off, Burns shows the full face of the bat and pushes it down through mid off. Cheteshwar Pujara sprints and puts in a slide as well near the fence but fails to pull it back.
Fuller and on middle, Burns defends it off his pads to the leg side.
FOUR! Put away! Rory Burns loves his runs on the leg side. Short in length and around middle, Burns swivels and pulls it in front of square leg for a boundary. 50 up for England.

FOUR! Siraj challenges the batsman again with a short delivery on middle, Rory accepts it, turns inside the crease and thumps it via another pull shot. It's in front of square leg and races away to the fence.
FOUR! A flurry of boundaries for England, their fourth in the last 5 balls. Short and wide outside off, Root stands back and slaps it through point for a boundary.
FOUR! Make it five in the last six balls. But this time it's off the outside edge. An inswinger around off, Root pushes inside the line and edges it through the gap at the slip cordon for a boundary.
Angling in from around off, Root defends it from the back foot.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Ishant gets a fuller length delivery to straighten around off, Root tries to defend but edges it behind. It's done with soft hands and hence it doesn't carry to Pant.
Outside off, left alone.
Too wide outside off, yet another easy leave for Joe. Testing over from Ishant.
FOUR! England continue to find the fence. Wrong line from Jasprit Bumrah, bowls a length ball on the pads and Burns puts it away through mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around off, Rory defends it off his back foot to the off side.
Fuller and on middle, flicked on the leg side to mid-wicket. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Good length delivery outside off, Burns removes his bat from the line.
Shortish and outside off, Burns rocks back to cut but finds the fielder square of the wicket on the off side.
Good leave. Full and around off, straightening off the seam, Burns lets it be.
Fuller delivery on off, angling in, Burns is behind the line as he defends it back towards the bowler.
Ishant delivers a length ball, on middle and leg, Root clips it wide of fine leg and returns for the second run.

FOUR! Superbly executed. Ishant offers width outside off, the length is a touch short, Root camps back and guides it wide of point. It races away as Jadeja gives the chase but it's going down the slope and crosses the fence in no time. The 50-run stand comes up. There is a third man coming in place now.
Presses forward to a full ball and pushes it defensively to covers.
Slants in a length ball around off, Joe brings down a straight bat in defense.
Beaten! It's around off and on a length, Root feels for it inside the line but misses. Didn't carry to Pant.
Fullish and close to off, Root solidly gets behind the line as he defends it to the off side.
Short in length and outside off, Burns stays back to guide it down to third man but finds gully.
Oohhh...Burns almost chops it back on. Bumrah delivers it around off, Rory decides to defend it but it takes the toe end and bounces over the stumps.
Shortish and just outside off, Burns tries to cut from the crease but it's too close to his body and he misses. He is beaten on the inside edge.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
A length ball, on middle and leg, Burns glances it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, outside off, Root taps it down from the crease to point.
Ishant puts it on a fuller length and just outside off, Burns defends it to point.
FOUR! Shot! Ishant overpitches outside off and Burns needs no second invitation. He leans into the drive and strokes it crisply through covers for a glorious boundary.
In the channel outside off, on a good length, Burns has nothing to do with it.
On a length and close to off, Burns gets behind the line and defends it down on the surface.
A loosener, very full and wide outside off, Burns doesn't go chasing after it.
Shortish and on off, moving back into the batsman with extra bounce, Rory tries working on the leg side but misses. It takes his thigh pad and deflects to the off side.
Good length ball outside off, Joe is on the front foot as he eases it through point for a single.
Back of a length, moving in from around off, Burns gets close to the delivery and defends it to the off side.
On a good length and around off, Burns defends it back to the bowler.
Drifting down the leg side, Burns is strong in that area as he tucks it through square leg for two.
Another delivery on middle, Rory flicks it in front of square leg for a single. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Ishant dives at backward point. Shortish and outside off, Root tries to cut it wide of the fielder but Sharma stops it with a dive.
Around off and on a good length, Root takes a positive stride forward and lets it go.
Floated and full on off, Burns is on the front foot in defense.
Advances down the track to a full ball and defends it back to the bowler.
Turning in from around off, Burns defends it off the inner edge to short leg.
Shout for an lbw! Floated one, full and outside off, Burns tries to sweep but misses. It hits him on the pads, they appeal but the impact is outside off.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Fires it flat and quick on middle, Burns goes back and defends it on the leg side. Wow, that over went in a flash.
Shortish length ball on off, Root defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Fuller in length and outside off, Root mistimes his drive back in the direction of the bowler.
A little short and outside off, Root stays back and guides it down to backward point. Finds Jadeja. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Crunched! Length ball on off, Root plays a perfect cover drive.
Good length ball on off, defended to covers.
Full and angling down, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Fullish and on middle, worked wide of short leg for a run.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Tossed up ball outside off, Burns tries to sweep but misses.
Very full and on middle, kept out to short leg.
Uses the spin on this delivery and helps it to square leg.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Short in length and outside off, punched square of the wicket on the off side for a couple of runs.
Shortish again, around off, dabbed down in the gap at covers for one.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Straying down the leg side, Burns tickles it through square leg for a single.
Again the line is too straight and this time Root works it through square leg to pick a single.
Siraj is yet to get his line right in this spell. Serves a length ball on the pads and Burns eases it towards mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and shorter on off, Burns punches it off his back foot to covers.
Fires a full ball on off, Burns flicks it to square leg for a single.
100 up for England! Floated ball, landing full around off, Root pushes it gently to cover-point and steals a single. Also, Root completes 2000 Test runs against India.
Shout for a bat-pad! Turning back in from around off, Burns tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to short leg. The Indians get excited but nothing from the umpire.
Flatter and on middle, quicker through the air, Burns hangs back and defends it on the leg side.
Loopy and around off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
A touch short and on off, jumping onto the batsman, Root is on his toes as he defends it down to gully.
Short and outside off, Root steers it to the left side of point and takes a sharp single.
Fuller in length on off, defended.
On middle, helped on the leg side but not in the gap.

Burns is safe! That has bounced in front of the fielder. Short in length and outside off, Burns goes back to cut but fails to middle it well. It goes down towards gully but is dying in front of Rahul. He goes down low to take the catch but is not sure if that carried. The umpire goes upstairs the replays find that it bounced.
Full and on middle, Burns pushes it down to mid on.
Fuller and on off, defended to the off side.
Fuller and straighter, worked in the gap at mid-wicket for a run.
A touch short and on off, Burns goes back and plays it down in front of short leg.
This time Rory gets back and nudges it wide of short leg for a single.
Clips a full ball to mid-wicket and takes a run. Wants two but not happening.
Flatter delivery, on off, Burns gets back to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Taps a length ball down to point and takes a single.
Fractionally short in length and on middle, Burns glances it to deep square leg for a single.
Extra bounce, from a length around off, Root goes back to defend and does so from the upper half of his blade.
Beaten all ends up! Full in length and outside off, Root opts to play the cover drive but it nips back in and beats the inside edge.
Siraj tries to repeat the last delivery but this time the line is very straight, Root clips it down to fine leg for a single.
Shortish and on middle, Burns tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Begins his spell with a good length delivery outside off, Burns allows it through to the keeper.

OUT! Rory Burns is caught plumb in front! Shami speeds in from 'round the wicket and lands it on a length close to off. The ball lands and jags back in to beat the attempted flick shot from Burns. He is pinged on the pads, the appeal is made and the finger has gone up. Rory takes the DRS but to no use. Only an inside edge could have saved him. But the bat is absent. The Ball Tracker shows THREE REDS. Burns departs late in the day, one short of his fifty. England trail by 256 runs.
Howout: lbw b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Full and on off, the batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
An overpitched delivery outside off, Bairstow allows it through.

FIVE RUNS! A length ball around off, Bairstow brings down a straight bat to defend but it takes the outer half and rolls to the left side of point. Jadeja attacks the ball, has a shy at the bowler's end as Bairstow goes for a run. It's a wayward throw and the mid on fielder probably was not expecting it to his left side, probably was anticipating a shy at the striker's end and was moving to his right. Boundary results.
Fuller length ball outside off, Root taps it down to covers and takes a single.
On a length and outside off, Root eases it down to third man for a run.
Fullish and outside off, Bairstow drives it off his front foot to covers.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Gets forward to a full all and blocks it to the off side.

Huge shout for a caught behind, not given! Excellent delivery, full and around off, straightening off the seam, Bairstow gets across the stumps, is squared up slightly in defense as it beats the bat. There is some sound as the ball goes to Pant and Siraj starts to celebrate. The umpire remains unmoved. The replays show that the noise was of the ball clipping the flap of the back pad. Rightly Kohli didn't waste any more review.
The line is wide outside off, Jonny shoulders arms.
On a length and outside off, Root plays late and places it wide of point for a run.
Fuller in length and on middle, Jonny clips it through square leg for a single.
Uses the angle of the bowler and works it in the gap on the leg side for one.
Good length delivery outside off, shaping in, JB offers no shot.
Full and swinging in around off, Bairstow gets on the front foot and defends it back.
Superb leave. Full in length and outside off, shaping in, Bairstow takes his front leg away from the line of stumps and then shoulders arms.
Root moves to 48! Full in length and on middle, nipping in, Root tries to flick but it takes the inner half and rolls to fine leg. They cross.
Close to off, on a good length, shaping in, Bairstow strides forward and across before defending it with a dead bat.
Beaten! Great ball again. On a length and outside off, holding its line, Jonny hangs his bat out in defense but the ball whistles past the outside edge.
Indipper this time, on a length around off, Jonny defends it from the inner half to the leg side.
Smart thinking from the bowler. Goes for an inswinging yorker, trying to catch the batsman off-guard, Jonny Bairstow does well to dig it out safely.
Fuller in length and on off, Bairstow defends it watchfully. That will be STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Shami begins with a fuller length ball, in the channel outside off and holding its line, Root makes a watchful leave.
England are away on Day 3. Shami hurls across a length ball close to off, Root plays it with gentle hands and uses an angled bat to run it down to third man for a single. Moves to 49!
Good leave from Jonny! Shows a positive stride forward, not too much but just enough to cover his stumps. The delivery is on a fuller length outside off, going straight on, it's left alone.
Fullish and angling in around off, there is definite movement, Bairstow gets forward and drives it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, moving back in with the slope, Jonny remains on the back foot and taps it down to point.
On a length and close to off, Bairstow is not entirely forward as he defends it to the off side.
Siraj starts with a fuller length ball on middle and leg, Root flick it to the right of mid-wicket and screams 'wait'.
Serves it on a fuller length outside off, getting it to move back in, Joe is on the front foot as he defends it to the off side.
Drifting down the leg side, Root fails to flick and it goes off his pads towards the keeper. Pant dives across to his left to stop the ball. Joe was eyeing a run but was sent back by Jonny.

Appeal for an lbw, not given. Fuller in length and outside off, an inswinger, Root draws forward to drive but misses and is pinged on the pads. They appeal but the umpire shakes his head. No DRS is taken by India. They have only one left. The impact was outside off, shows the replay.

FOUR! Fifty for Root and the crowd goes Roooooooooot! Another fine knock from the English skipper. A length ball on off, Root presses forward and drives it crisply through cover-point for a boundary. Can he get a big score here?
Fuller in length and on middle, Root knocks it down to mid on to complete the over.
Good length ball outside off, holding its line, Jonny feels for it and gets beaten.
Movement away from the batsman, drawing Bairstow into the shot. The batter tries to feel the ball but gets beaten.

FOUR! Nicely timed! Fuller in length and around middle and leg, Bairstow picks it off his pads and flicks it beautifully through square leg. Siraj sprints across to his left, puts in a dive and reaches the ball as well but it bounces over his hands to reach the fence.
Fuller and closer to off, Bairstow gets forward and defends it with an angled bat to the off side.
FOUR! Streaky! Shami delivers it full and outside off, seaming away, Bairstow looks to drive but gets a big fat outside edge. It races quickly past Rahane at gully for a boundary.
This one is angled into the batsman, going on with the slope, Bairstow defends it from the crease to mid on. Two boundaries from this over, England trail by 232 runs.
Fuller in length and around off, Root drives it down the ground but finds the mid on fielder.

Siraj serves it full and around off, shaping in, Root flicks it across the line and once it beats the diving mid-wicket fielder, the batsmen take three runs. The mid on fielder chases it down near the boundary line.
On a length and around off, Jonny turns his wrists and pushes it softly in front of the widish mid on fielder for a quick run.
On a length and around middle, Root works it with the angle of the bowler but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Good length ball close to off, Root stays back and tries to run it down to third man but finds gully.
Fuller and on off, shaping in, Root offers a straight bat in defense.
Good length ball on off, Jonny covers all his stumps as he defends it down to mid-wicket.
A stifled appeal! Shami goes wide of the crease and hurls in a length ball around off, angling in, Bairstow tries to hit it across the line but possibly gets an inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR! Slightly edgy. Full in length and around off, Bairstow presses forward to defend and his bottom hand comes off the handle. There is a soft outside edge generated and it takes the ball away from gully for a boundary at third man.

FOUR! Best shot of the morning from Jonny! Shami delivers it full and just outside off, Bairstow strides forward and brings down a straight bat to caress it past the bowler for a boundary. Very straight.
Fuller and on off, Bairstow defends it solidly off the front foot.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
In the channel outside off, Root plays his pet shot and runs it down to third man for a single.
A length ball landing around off, Bairstow stays back and uses the angle of the bowler to keep it out towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! What a shot! These are signs that the pitch is a great one for batting. A nice half-volley outside off, Jonny drives it through the line and picks the gap at mid off for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off, angling in, Bairstow turns inside the crease and helps it down to fine leg for a run. 150 up for England.
Fuller in length and on off, Root is firmly behind the line as he offers a solid defensive shot.
Identical to the last delivery, once again Root is forward to defend it towards mid off. The current stand is now worth 42 runs.
Shami digs in a short ball around off, Jonny walks forward and across before pulling it to deep square leg for a single.
Pitches it up and close to off, Root takes his front foot forward and defends it to covers.
Edgy! Fuller again, close to off, Root tries to push it through covers off his front foot but it takes a soft outside edge. Doesn't carry to gully.
Good length ball on off, Root goes on the back foot and defends it down on the surface.
Shami goes slightly fuller and on off, Root stays back and offers a straight bat in defense.
Width outside off, Root stays back and dabs it down through point for a single.
Good length ball on middle, angling in, Root gets behind the line and defends it to mid on.
Siraj lands it fuller and outside off, shaping in, Root brings his bat and pad together as he pushes it towards cover-point.

Sharp movement and extra bounce. This one lands outside off, on a length and hurries up the batsman. Root fails to work it around and is hit on the thigh pad. Joe has no idea where the ball is, wants a run but Bairstow can see the ball is near the slip cordon and sends his skipper back.
Straighter in line, it's worked through square leg for a single.
Bouncer this time from Mohammed Siraj, around middle, Jonny picks it early and lets it be.
Fuller in length and outside off, nipping back in, Bairstow isn't forward enough as he tries to drive. Probably gets an inside edge onto the pads as it deflects to the off side.
FOUR BYES! Wrong start from Bumrah, sprays a length delivery way down the leg side. Root fails to work it away and Pant has no chance of collecting it. A boundary at fine leg.
On a length and outside off, Root defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Good length ball on off, Root stays on the back foot and defends it down safely.
Slightly short and around off, Root stays back and works it through mid-wicket for a run. The 50-run stand comes up between this pair.
Beaten! That's the line. On and around off, a length delivery, angling in, Bairstow tries to defend but is beaten on the outside edge.
Full in length and outside off, angling in, Jonny defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Floated and full around off, Root lunges and defends it back.
Fuller and flatter around off, defended off the front foot to cover-point.
Slower through the air, nice loop, it's full and on middle, Root defends it on the leg side.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one, on middle and leg, Root gently taps it down in front of square leg and steals a run.
Flatter trajectory, full and on off, Jonny is on the front foot as he defends it to the leg side.
Good length ball, around off, Root plays late with an open face and taps it down to point. The call is to 'wait'.

Slightly short and on middle, Root hangs on the back foot, uses the angle of the bowler and works it through square leg for a single. The fielder (Ishant Sharma) has a wayward shy at the keeper's end. It goes over the leaping Rishabh Pant and the fielder behind him fails to collect the ball. The batsmen get one overthrow.
Fuller in length and outside off, Joe is on the front foot in defense.
Back of a length, outside off, Root leans back and cuts it off the outer half but it drops in front of gully.
Fuller and around off, shaping in, Joe strides forward and eases it with gentle hands. Once it beats the backward point fielder, they cross.
Around off on a length, Bairstow closes the face of his bat and works it wide of mid on for a run.
Quicker and fuller on middle, defended on the leg side.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Bairstow defends it off his front foot.
Skidding down the leg side, Bairstow helps it off his pads behind square leg for one.
Fuller and outside off, driven off the front foot to covers.
Fires in an arm ball, a touch short and skidding in from around off, Root goes deep inside the crease and defends it to the off side.
Slightly short and on off, Root goes back and comfortably nurdles it in front of square leg for a single.
Bumrah pitches it up and outside off to start a new over, Root drives it down the ground but straight to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Root hangs on the back foot and defends it towards cover-point.
Identical to the last delivery, angling in from around off, Root is forward as he blocks it to covers.
Delivers it on a length again, keeping his line around off, Root offers a defensive blade as he keeps it out towards extra cover.
Fuller in length and around off, shaping in, Root is forward as he defends it with an inside edge to the leg side.
Back of a length, angling in, Root again defends it watchfully to the off side. Maiden!
FOUR! A lovely lap sweep! Too full in length and close to off, Jonny Bairstow premediates his paddle sweep and nails it wide of the short fine leg fielder for a boundary.
Quicker one, flat and around off, skidding in, Bairstow goes back to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and on middle, skidding in, Bairstow gets forward and works it behind square leg for a single.
Loopy and full around off, Root strides forward to meet the ball and jams it down. Called a no ball for overstepping.

Skidding in from around off, Root works it off his pads on the leg side and sets off for a single. Slight hesitation shown by Joe but Jonny runs to the other end with full force. Mohammed Siraj attacks the ball from mid-wicket, dives forward and has a shy at the striker's end. Misses.
Flatter and on middle, helped to square leg for a single.
Beats the outside edge! Bumrah lands it on a length and outside off, angling in, Bairstow tries to defend but the ball beats the outside edge.
And again! Bumrah delivers it on a good length outside off, Bairstow has a needless poke inside the line and misses.
Angles in a length ball on off, Bairstow defends it close to his body and keeps it out safely.
Sharp delivery, landing on a length outside off and jagging in, Bairstow walks across as he tries to defend. Misses and is pinged on the back thigh.
On and around off, a length delivery, Jonny defends it with an angled bat to point.
Edged! On the bounce to Rohit at gully. Good length delivery outside off, Bairstow pushes inside the line and gets a soft outside edge. It drops in front of Sharma.
Fuller and on off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and flighted on off, defended off the front foot to the off side.
Loopy and full on off, Root gets forward and gently helps it through square leg for a single.
Fires it in, very full and on middle, it's blocked back to the bowler.
Skidding down the leg side, Jonny moves back and tries to flick but misses.
Tossed up delivery, pitched full around off, Jonny pushes it down to mid on.
On a length, outside off, Joe Root pushes it towards point.
Ahhh... this is pitched up, inviting the drive outside off, Root accepts the invitation but is late on the drive. Is beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! Very productive area for Joe Root. Outside off, on a length, stays a tad low, Root gets inside the line and dabs it on the bounce, to the right of a diving first slip, to the third man fence. The deficit is now 186.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.

Identical delivery to the third one of this over, the skipper lunges to push this time. The ball goes off the outer half of the bat, again wide of first slip. But this time, the man who was at gully then, is stationed at second slip and he stops it.
Outside off, Joe pushes it behind point for a single.
Full, outside off, Joe Root drives it straight to short extra cover.
Quicker, shorter, on middle, Root defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller, around off, Root works it towards short mid-wicket.
Fired in around off, the skipper goes back and blocks.
You really don't want to concede that. Full, outside off, Joe just pushes it to the right of Mohammed Shami at backward point, looks up at his partner, Jonny Bairstow and takes a single.
Around off, Jonny Bairstow works it towards backward square leg.
Outside off, on a length, Joe Root looks to tap and run to the off side but the ball shapes back in, takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Outside off, on a length again, Root dabs it behind point for a single. Wants the second but is sent back.
Fuller, outside off, Jonny Bairstow pushes it straight to point. 429 balls left in the day.
Outside off, coming in with the angle, Bairstow shoulders arms.
Bumrah goes wide of the crease, it is angled into middle, defended.
On off, Bairstow pushes it to mid off.
On middle, Root blocks it out.
A huge appeal, it lands on the leg, it goes on with the arm, Root looks to flick but misses and it hits him on the pads. Going down leg perhaps.
Full, around middle, Jonny Bairstow works it towards short mid-wicket.
On middle, Bairstow hangs back and defends it.
Full, around middle, Jonny Bairstow works it towards short mid-wicket.
Full again, Bairstow drives it straight to mid on.
Starts off with a no ball. Oversteps and lands it on a length outside off, Joe Root drops it down in front of his feet and takes the single.
Full and straight, Jonny Bairstow works it towards short mid-wicket. 419 balls left in the day.
Down the leg side, fuller in length, Bairstow gets across and looks to whip but misses.
Outside off, Jonny lunges and presses it with an open face behind point for a run. The deficit is now 179.
Too full, outside off, Root gets across, nearly falls over but manages to flick it behind square leg for one.
Outside off, pushed to the off side.
Full, just outside off, Jonny Bairstow walks forward and defends it towards cover.
Full, outside off, Joe Root pushes it towards point.

This one rears off a length, outside off, Root is caught by surprise and his bottom hand comes off the bat as he looks to flick. The ball goes off the gloves behind square leg. Rishabh Pant himself runs after the ball to stop it. A single taken.

Excellent running and the crowd applauds. Full, around off, Jonny Bairstow tucks it through mid-wicket with the softest hands possible and then runs hard with the strongest intent possible. The fielder from deep backward square leg gets to the ball to his left but two runs are taken by then. The stand moves to 81, of which Bairstow is 41.
Too straight, clipped towards fine leg for a run.
Full, outside off, Root drives it straight to mid off. 409 balls left in the day.
Full and straight, driven straight back to the bowler.
Around middle and off, Jonny Bairstow gets across and defends it towards mid on.
Great delivery. Pitched fractionally short of fuller length, outside off, Bairstow looks to defend but the ball then shapes away at the last moment, to beat the outside edge.
On a length, outside off, Jonny shoulders arms.
Full, around off, JB gets across and pushes it towards mid on.
Outside off, on a length, Jonny Bairstow lets it pass.
A bit too straight, Bairstow tucks it through mid-wicket. The fielder from the 30-yard circle gets after it, slides and stops the ball near the ropes. Two runs taken.
Full, outside off, pretty wide, Joe Root leans and drives it aerially through the covers. KL Rahul sweeps it across to his right in the deep from point and keeps the batsmen to a single.
On a length, around middle and leg, Jonny Bairstow helps it towards fine leg for a run.
This is on a length, angled in from off stump, Root looks to turn it to the leg side but plays a bit early. Gets a leading edge towards point. 399 balls left in the day.
Outside off, on a length again, this time the skipper defends solidly.
Outside off, on a length, Joe shoulders arms. The ball wobbles quite a bit after pitching.
This one scoots through. Full, outside off, JR looks to defend but the ball just goes beneath the bat and goes behind. Good keeping by Rishabh Pant.
On a length, outside off, Jonny Bairstow steers it behind point for a single. The deficit is now 169.
On a length, outside off, Joe Root punches it through cover for a couple.
Down the leg side, Root misses his flick.
Outside off, punched to the off side for a run. The stand moves to 90.

200 COMES UP FOR ENGLAND. They trail by 163 now. Short and outside off, Bairstow punches it through the covers. The fielder gets to the ball in the deep from point, to his right,  but while sliding, he  slips. The batsmen take the third on the throw.
Outside off, solidly defended.

FIVE WIDES! That is a monster for Rishabh Pant. A short ball, around off, Jonny Bairstow thinks about the pull but then bails out. The ball pitches, rises and then moves away late. Poor Pant leaps full stretch to his right, gets a glove to it but still can only parry it to the third man fence. The deficit is now 158.
This one is down the leg side now. Short again, Bairstow lets it be, after initially thinking about the pull. An easier take for Pant this time. 389 balls left in the day.
Full, outside off, driven down the ground. Mid off cuts it off to his right.
Around off, coming in, solidly defended.
Full, outside off, swinging away, Jonny looks to drive but the late movement induces an outside edge which goes behind point. A single taken.
Full, outside off, Joe Root gets a big stride and defends it towards cover.
100-STAND IS UP IN 180 BALLS! Excellent partnership. Outside off, on a length, Root waits for the ball to come and then plays it late behind point for a run.
Full on middle, Joe Root works it to the right of Jasprit Bumrah at mid on for a single.

50 UP FOR JONNY BAIRSTOW! In 90 balls. An important knock in the context of the game and in the context of his red-ball career. This means a lot to him as his reaction suggests. He takes a while to soak in the applause and then walks across to raise his bat. It is not a century but when you cross 50 for the first time in 19 innings, emotions flow. Full, on middle, Bairstow walked across and flicked it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full, around off, Joe Root pushes it towards mid off.
Full again, Root walks across and defends solidly towards mid on.
Very full, outside off, the skipper drives it towards mid on. 379 balls left in the day.

Full, outside off, Joe defends it towards cover. He immediately looks up at the umpire, perhaps hoping for the bails to be taken off, but nope, there is a minute left on the clock. We will have time for another over before Lunch.
A length ball, around middle, Jonny Bairstow walks across and helps it towards fine leg for a single.
Full, outside off, hint of away swing, Joe Root defends solidly.
FOUR! Completely off line from Mohammed Shami and he is disappointed with himself. Down the leg side, on a length, Root gets across and tickles it to the fine leg fence. The deficit is now 149.
Full, outside off, the skipper defends it solidly towards gully.
Just outside off, fractionally short of full, Joe blocks it towards cover.
A WICKET-LESS SESSION FOR ENGLAND! The last ball is allowed to pitch on a length outside off and is then steered behind point for a single. LUNCH ON DAY 3, ENGLAND 216/3, TRAIL BY 148!
Starts with a loopy full ball on off, Root is on the front foot as he defends it back.
Jadeja goes flatter and delivers it on middle, Joe moves back and turns it behind square leg for one.
Floated one, full and outside off, Bairstow draws forward and defends it to the off side.
Well stopped! Too full and around off, it's driven to covers where Kohli makes a tumbling stop.
Flights it and lands it on middle, Jonny strides forward to block it back.
Arm ball, around middle and leg, Bairstow works it off his pads towards short fine leg, finds the fielder and Root turns down the single.
Begins with a short delivery down the leg side, Root tries to pull but it goes below his bat. Pant dives across to his left to collect the ball but it pops out. Anyway, there was no bat or glove.
A bouncer on middle and leg, Root shapes up for the pull shot but then decides against it.
Siraj continues to dig it on, short and around middle and leg, Root this time goes through with his attempted pull shot but fails to connect. A half-shout from the bowler but nothing doing.
Short again, going down the leg side, Root pulls but doesn't connect too well. Still, it rolls behind square leg and they cross. Moves to 91!
A half-tracker to Jonny as well, down the leg side, Bairstow shoulders arms and lets it be.
Back of a length, around off, Bairstow gets across and defends it down on the leg side. An effort over from Siraj.
Loopy and full around off, Root drives it off his front foot to covers.
Full and floated, this one is wider outside off and Root caresses it to deep cover for a single.
Identical to the last delivery and Bairstow this time pushes it through the gap at covers for one.
Fires it full and down the leg side, Root works it off his pads but finds the backward square leg fielder.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Root draws forward and defends it to covers.
Slightly flat this time, full and around off, once again Root pushes it defensively to covers. Another over of Jadeja passes by in the blink of an eye.
Siraj begins this over as well with a bouncer. Seems like a slower one around off, Bairstow ducks.
Wayward bouncer on this occasion. Bairstow offers no shot and it lobs off his left shoulder. It balloons to the left of Rishabh Pant and who runs across and then collects the ball.

FOUR! Dangerous shot! Short and on middle, angling down, Bairstow turns inside the crease with the pull shot, gets a bit of top edge and it just beats the flying Rishabh Pant to his left. This seems like a definite ploy from Siraj after Lunch. The movement of Pant also suggests so.
Short around leg, Bairstow takes his front leg up and pulls it down to fine leg for a run.
Effort delivery, a bouncer but down the leg side, Root just watches it go after setting himself to play. That's the right way to approach it. No need to overcommit.
Angles in a length ball on middle, Root brings down a straight bat and bunts it in front of mid on. They cross for a run.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball and drives it to Kohli at covers.
Floated and full on off, Root defends it by leaning forward.
Flatter and a bit shorter, Joe goes deep inside the crease and defends it to the off side.
Quicker delivery, full and around middle, Root nudges it in front of square leg and looks for a run. The fielder though reacts quickly to his right and the single has to be aborted.
Presses forward to a full ball and drives it square of the wicket on the off side for a run.
Arrows in a quicker one, flat and on middle, Bairstow moves back and defends it down. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Oohhh...that went past the outside edge. Flatter delivery, landing full around off, Bairstow tries to defend but it straightens just a little to beat the outside edge.
Digs in a short ball around middle, Root gets on top of the bounce and rolls his wrists over his pull shot. It speeds down to fine leg and they take a run. There is a leg slip in place now.
A bumper around middle and leg, Jonny knows the plan from the bowler and ducks.

Siraj goes short but down the leg side, Bairstow moves across a bit and then lets it be. This tactic to bowl short around leg will only work if the batsmen also try to be adventurous. Otherwise, it's quite easy to neglect this line.

OUT! The ploy to bowl short has worked and India have a breakthrough. Bairstow will be very disappointed to walk into the trap. Mohammed Siraj switches to 'round the wicket and digs in a short ball around leg, Jonny turns to pull but the ball jumps a bit extra to kiss his gloves. The ball loops in the air and Virat Kohli walks ahead from first slip to accept a simple catch. The 121-run stand is broken and England trail by 135 runs. What a moment to lose a wicket with the second new ball just around the corner. India will be smelling blood now.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Good length ball on off, angling in, Buttler defends it off his back foot.
Spears in a very full ball on middle, Buttler tries to flick but it takes the inner edge and runs down to fine leg. Jos opens his account with a single.

Big appeal for an lbw, not given! This one looks very leg side. Virat has a word with his keeper and then decides not to take the referral. Quicker one, full and around leg, Buttler tries to flick but misses. He is rapped on the pads, but not given. The replays show that it's skidding down and would have clipped the leg pole. Umpire's call would have stayed.
Flatter and shorter on middle, defended off the back foot to the off side.
Tossed up ball and around off, pushed off the front foot to covers.
Very full and around off, Jos forces it down to mid off where the fielder slides and misfields. Gives away a single.
Too full and on middle, Root eases it to the right of mid on and crosses.
Slower and fuller on middle, driven to mid off.
Too full and outside off, Root keeps it out towards covers.
Short in length and wide outside off, Root drops his wrists and allows it through.
Serves it full and outside off, a bit of swing, Root drives but finds mid off.
Pitches it up and outside off, Root looks for a drive away from his body but meets it with the bottom part of his bat. Ends up mistiming it back to the bowler.
Extra bounce with movement. On a length around off, Root fails to defend and is hit on the thigh pad. There is a bit there for the seamers.

Finally hits it from the meat of the bat. Full and outside off, Root crunches his drive through cover-point. The fielder in the deep runs across to his right and stops it inches away from the rope. Three taken, Root moves to 99.
Starts with a length ball close to off, angling in, Root goes on the back foot and pushes it out to covers.
Drops it on a length and outside off, Root plays it down with an angled bat to the right of gully.

HUNDRED FOR JOE ROOT! The crowd roars - Roooooooooooooooooooooooootttttt.... The England captain has stroked yet another century, his 22nd in Tests. Good length ball around off, Joe taps it down towards cover-point and rushes to the other end. The fielder misses his shy at the striker's end and Root raises his bat to soak in the applause from this capacity crowd at Lord's. What a player!
A length delivery outside off, Buttler plays it down from the back foot to covers and picks up a single.

EDGY FOUR! Back of a length, outside off, straightening off the seam with extra bounce, Root has a poke inside the line and edges it wide of the diving second slip fielder for a boundary. Root needs to get his composure back. England are not out of the woods, yet.
Width outside off, short in length, Root runs it down fine to third man and collects a couple of runs.
A gentle delivery, on a length and wide outside off, Buttler allows it through. It's important for Sharma to not waste the second new ball.
Better line. On a length around off and shaping back in, Buttler is on his toes as he defends it to mid-wicket.

Chipped in the air and it goes just over extra cover. Fuller in length and outside off, shooting of the surface, Buttler tries to drive but it takes the higher half of his blade and balloons over Shami. The batsmen take three runs. Shami needed the height of Ishant Sharma to catch that.
Back of a length, around off and jumping extra, Root jumps to control the bounce and guides it down to third man for a run.
Good length ball on off, Buttler blocks it solidly from the crease.
Good length again, around off and once again there is some extra lift off the surface, Jos does well to defend it down from the back foot.

Movement off the pitch. Shortish and on middle, nipping in, Root tries to defend but it takes the inside half and runs down to fine leg. The fielder runs across to collect the ball and the batters take two.
On a good length and outside off, shaping away a shade, Root covers his stumps and shoulders arms.

Beautiful delivery, around full length outside off and shaping away, Root takes his front leg forward, thinks about driving but then leaves. Called a no ball for overstepping. Quite tight, as the replays suggest.
Strides forward to a length ball and defends it to the off side.
Bumrah goes fuller and closer to off, Root is on the front foot as he pushes it to covers.
A little bit of width, shortish length, Root plays late and runs it down to third man for a single. Pure skills of Root, not easy to do that.
Spears it in, full and around off, Buttler offers a straight bat and checks his shot. Pushes it down the track defensively.
Some swing for Ishant. Full and curling in from around off, Root leans across and works it to the right side of mid on for a run.
Back of a length, in the zone outside off, a good leave from Buttler. There was plenty of movement once the ball left the batter.
Again it's a touch short and this time it's closer to off, Buttler has to offer a shot and he defends it down near the surface.
Quite wide on this occasion, a touch short again, Buttler has nothing to do with it.

Shout for a caught behind The umpire stays still. Was there a little edge? Did it carry? Nothing from the umpire, India decide not to review. A length delivery outside off, shaping in, Buttler tries to defend from the front foot but misses. It clips his pads and goes behind to the keeper. So, we know from where the sound came. Also, the impact was easily outside off. Good to see Kohli not moving an inch once the appeal was turned down.
Taps a length ball from the crease to cover-point. No single available.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it from the back foot to the off side.

FOUR! 9000 Test runs for Joe Root. A length delivery on middle and leg, Root clips it off his pada and it races behind square leg. Ishant Sharma sprints across to his left, puts in an old-school slide and it goes through his legs to the fence. The giant screen flashes about Joe's milestone and the crowd gets another chance to go Roooooooooootttttttt...

The line is straight again, Root tucks it through square leg and Ishant once again is sprinting across to his left with the partisan crowd in that section making a lot of noise. This time no mistake from the tall man and England get two.
Beaten! On a good length outside off, shaping away, Root pushes inside the line and misses.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Angling in from around off, Root defends it from the back foot.

FOUR! Not from the middle of the bat but still a boundary. Fuller in length and outside off, shaping in, Buttler tries to play the off drive but it nips back in to take the inner half. Still the connection is enough to take the ball past the boundary line at long on.
Short and wide outside off, Jos cuts but finds the point fielder.
A length delivery wide outside off, shaping away, Buttler shoulders arms.
Shami gets closer to the off stump as he delivers an outswinger, Buttler covers his stumps and leaves.
There is the indecisiveness for Jos Buttler outside off. It's a length ball outside off, Buttler stays back to push at it but the ball shapes in and beats the inside half of his blade.

FOUR! Gorgeous shot! Back of a length, around off, Buttler sits on the back foot and crunches it through covers. It goes up the hill but the force of the shot takes it beyond the rope. Buttler moves to 14 and this stand is worth 37 in no time. The deficit drops down, it's under 100 now.
Bumrah spears in a full ball on middle and leg, angling down, Root tries to flick but doesn't middle it properly. It goes off his pads to square leg and they take a leg bye.
Fullish and on off, Buttler drives it back to the bowler who collects it on one bounce and mimes a throw at the batter.
Bumrah keeps probing with a fuller length delivery around off, Jos is forward as he defends it to the off side.
Lands it full and outside off, pretty gentle, Buttler opens the face of his bat and pushes it to point.
Good length delivery landing outside off and shaping in, Buttler stays on the back foot and defends it towards mid on.
Slightly fuller and outside off, moving back in, Jos takes a long stride forward before leaving it. Doesn't carry to Rishabh.
Good start to the over, on a length and outside off, Root is forward to defend but it holds its line and beats the edge.
Pitches it up and close to off, Root plays the cover drive but finds the fielder.
Ishant goes fuller but also straighter, it's worked easily through square leg for a single by Root.
Shortish and close to off, angling in, Buttler moves back and helps it with gentle hands to square leg.
In the right channel, the batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

FOUR! Well played in the end! Sharma bowls it very full and around off, Buttler goes for the drive and he intentionally opens the face of his bat at the point of contact. The ball races away through point and Mohammed Siraj gives it a chase. He puts in a dive near the fence but fails to pull it back.
Full in length and on middle, Root defends it down the ground. Called a no ball for overstepping, not the first time Bumrah has done that.
Back of a length, around off, defended from the back foot to the off side.
Angling in from a length outside off, Root goes back and keeps it out towards mid-wicket. An easy run is taken.
Fractionally short and on top of off, Buttler goes on the back foot and plays it down to covers.
Very full and on middle, Jos gets behind the line of the delivery and pushes it to mid on.

EDGED AND FOUR! Bumrah puts it on a fuller length outside off, getting it to hold its line, Buttler decides to drive but gets a genuine outside edge through the gap between slips and gully for a boundary. Another no ball from Jasprit.
Taps a length ball down to point and pinches a single. The 50-run stand comes up and it has come off at a run rate of 4.5.
Play and a miss! Back of a length, outside off, skidding off the surface, Root flirts with it, away from his body and misses. Another no ball, third in the over.
Shortish and outside off, Root forces it from the back foot through point for a run.
Easy pickings! Full in length and outside off, Root eases it through backward point for a single.
Ishant serves it full and around off, getting it to shape in, Buttler tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length, on off, angling in, Buttler defends it from the back foot to the off side. Again the umpire watches the danger area and this time has a quiet word with the bowler.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Hurls in a length delivery in the channel outside off, not doing much off the seam, Buttler covers his stumps and shoulders arms.

OUT! SOUND OF TIMBER! Ishant roars. Big wicket for India as yet another partnership was building. A good length delivery landing just outside off, Buttler tries to defend the line but it jags back in with the slope, beats the bat and hits the top of off stump. A dream wicket for any fast bowler. A scratchy stay for Jos Buttler is over. England trail by 81 runs.
Howout: b Ishant Sharma

Commentary: FOUR! Glorious! Fuller in length and outside off, Root leans forward and drives it with all the elegance in the world. Finds the gap between mid off and extra cover for a boundary. Lovely timing, lovely placement, lovely balance. Joe Root is regal.
Fuller and on middle, Root tickles it to mid-wicket and speeds to the other end. The fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end. Slightly risky, no need to do that.

Shami delivers it from 'round the wicket, on a length and outside off, Moeen allows it through. A catching 45 is in place along with a fielder in the deep on the leg side. Moeen is another good candidate who doesn't like facing short deliveries.
Back of a length, outside off and angling in, Ali drops his wrists and allows it through to the keeper.
This one is more on a driving length outside off, Ali plants his front foot forward and then makes a leave.
Here comes the short delivery, around middle and leg, hurries the batsman slightly, Moeen somehow fends it away safely.
Short in length and on off, Root swivels on the back leg and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Very full and on off, angling in from 'round the wicket angle, Moeen brings his bat down and pushes it out to mid on.
Serves it on a length around off, Moeen prefers to sit back on the back foot as he defends it towards mid off.
On a length and outside off, Moeen has an easy leave on this occasion.
In the channel outside off, on a length again and straightens off the seam, Ali covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Moeen opens his account. Good length ball on off, Ali goes back and pushes it with soft hands to covers. They steal a single.
Digs it in short, around off, Moeen sways away from the line of the delivery. A good technique shown, bends his knees, drops his wrists while leaving.
Loose attempt from Ali. Back of a length and outside off, Moeen stays back to flay at it but misses.
Better this time from England's number 7. On a length and outside off, shaping away, a good leave by Moeen.
Superb line. Comes in with the angle around off and just holds its line, Ali pushes inside the line and misses.
Movement into the batsman. On a length around off, shaping in, Moeen decides to defend but it takes the inner edge and rolls behind towards short fine leg.
Beautiful delivery. A touch short and just outside off, nipping away, Moeen goes to feel the ball and gets beaten.
Siraj begins his new spell with a fuller length ball on middle, Root flicks it through backward square leg and picks up a run.
Angling across the left-hander, on a fuller length, Moeen makes a watchful leave. Siraj would love to test Moeen with shorter stuff.
Betaen completely! Back of a length, outside off and angling away, Moeen tries to punch it from the back foot but misses.
Big movement there. Full and outside off, Moeen leaves and it curves away as it reaches the keeper. Rishabh Pant collects it with a dive to his left.
Good length and on off, Moeen punches it from the back foot to mid off. The timing was not there.
A length ball on off, angling away, Ali shoulders arms. So, not a single short delivery was attempted.
Edgy from Root! Fuller in length around leg, straightening a bit, Root tries to flick but it takes the leading edge and goes through point for a single.
Full in length and on off, Moeen shows the full face of the bat and caresses it down to long off. Mayank Agarwal (sub) chases it and slides near the fence to save a run.
Fuller in length and on off, Root defends it off the inner half to the leg side.
Around off, on a fuller length, Joe presses forward with an angled bat and pushes it out to cover-point.

Fractionally short and close to off, Root moves back and plays it late as he tries to guide it towards third man. The gully fielder runs across to his right, dives but the ball evades him. A single is taken.

FOUR! Nice touch shot. Shortish delivery, outside off, Moeen stays back and opens the face of the bat at the last moment. Uses the pace of the bowler and guides it wide of point for a boundary. 300 up for England, they trail by 64 runs. The third hundred for England has been the quickest, off 157 balls.
Fuller in length and around off, Root defends it close to his front pad and pushes it to mid on.
Too full in length and on middle, Root picks it off his pads and flicks it down towards long leg for a run.
Around off on a length, straightening just a bit, Moeen pushes inside the line and misses.
FOUR! Moeen has done it again! It's short and a little bit wide outside off, Moeen stands back, uses his hands to attack the width and smashes it through cover-point.
Good length ball close to off, Moeen allows the ball to come to him and then defends it to the off side.

FOUR! Moeen is loving his shots square of the wicket on the off side. Short and wide outside off, Ali camps back and whacks it through point for a boundary. 55 is the deficit now as the stand moves to 26.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Not for the first time that has happened. Shami delivers it around off, on a good length, Root pushes inside the line from the back foot and edges it behind. It drops in front of Kohli at first slip and sneaks past him. The batters take a run.
A length ball around off, shaping away, Moeen allows it through.
Good length delivery, in the channel outside off, Ali drops his hands and lets it be.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A touch short in length around middle, angling down, Moeen stays back and only needs a tickle to send it fine. He does that and fetches a boundary at fine leg.
Back of a length, angling in from around off, Ali defends it from the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Moeen defends it solidly from the back foot. That will be TEA ON DAY 3!
Bumrah goes for a yorker but it ends up being a leg-stump half-volley, Root clips it through square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Fuller in length and on off, angling in, Root leans across and flicks it wide of mid on. Siraj dives to stop the ball and they cross for a single.
A touch short and on off, from 'round the wicket to Moeen, he works it with his wrists and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Gentle delivery, on a length close to off and straightening from there, Moeen covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Targets the stumps and slants in a length ball, Moeen offers a straight blade as he defends it to mid on.
Slightly fuller and closer to off, Moeen defends it with soft hands to cover-point and lets out a big scream of 'no run'.
Good length ball on top of off, Root sticks back, plays it late and taps it down in front of gully.
A touch short and on off, Joe is once again on the back foot as he keeps it out safely to the off side.
Too full in length this time, around off and angling in, Root brings down a straight bat and pushes it out from the inner half to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Root goes on his toes and defends it down onto the surface.
Shami keeps probing with a length delivery close to off, Root goes on the back foot to defend but it takes the inside half and strikes him on the pads.
Shortish and on off, Root loves that sort of a length, goes back and chops it through point for a single.
Full in length and on middle, Root uses the angle of the bowler and defends it with gentle hands to mid on.

Appeal for a run out! Fuller in length and around off, Root looks to defend but gets an inside edge. It rolls to square leg and they decide to steal a run. Axar Patel (sub) attacks the ball, has one stump to aim at and he finds it. The ball deflects to third man and they pinch another. Patel appeals for a run out, it's referred upstairs but Moeen is safely in.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Fuller again, on middle, Root flicks it to mid-wicket where Siraj misfields. It's down the slope and the batters collect three runs.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away, Ali drops his wrists and allows it through.
In the channel close to off, holding its line, Ali guars his stumps by covering the line as he shoulders arms.

Beats the bat! Just enough movement is still available to even beat the bat of the centurion. Fuller in length and around off, angling in and moving out, Root tries to defend but is beaten all ends up.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it towards mid-wicket.
Shortish and outside off, curling away, Root leaves it alone and Pant stretches his right hand out to collect the ball with a dive.
Good length ball on top of off, Root punches it from the back foot to covers.
Pitches it up and around off, Joe drives it to the left of mid off and takes a single.
Slightly short and close to off, the angle takes the ball into the left-hander, Moeen goes on the back foot and blocks.
Some extra bounce there as it jags back in from a good length outside off, Root fails to keep it out and is hit on the thigh pad.
A touch short and wide outside off, shaping in, Root rocks back, shaping up for the square cut but doesn't go for it.
This time Root goes for it! Short and wide and he cuts it through point for a single.
Bumrah serves one on a driving length outside off, Moeen offers no shot.
Shortish and sliding down the leg side, Moeen allows it through and Pant dives across to his right to collect the ball.
This time it's in the corridor outside off, Moeen is calmly sitting on the back foot as he makes another leave.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Root pushes it to covers.
Tosses it up and lands it full on off, Root is forward again in defense.
Flatter and shorter outside off, Root goes for the cut shot but it takes the bottom edge. The ball lands and bounces over first slip for a couple of runs.
Floated and full on off, Root lunges and bring his bat in front of the pads in defense.
Flatter and quicker on off, Root brings his bat and pad together as he defends it out to the off side.
Loopy delivery, full and on off, Root leans forward to block it again.
Bouncer on middle, Moeen just allows it to go over.
Good length delivery close to off, holding its line, Moeen is very watchful at the moment as he leaves.
