Bumrah serves one targeting the off stump, a length ball, Moeen pushes it from the crease to covers.
Bumrah is bowling some good lines here. He puts this one on a fuller length around off, angling in a bit, Moeen allows it through.
Bumrah bowls a bumper, around off, no issues for Moeen as he ducks.
Good length ball close to off, Moeen taps it down to cover-point and pinches a single.
Flatter one, landing short on off, Moeen goes back and plays it down, off the inner edge, in front of short leg.
Tossed up ball landing full around off, Moeen presses forward in defense.
Flighted and full on off, Moeen strides forward and pushes it with the spin to the leg side.
Too full in length and on off, it's driven back to the bowler.
Grip and turn, from around off, Moeen goes for the front foot defense but it takes the inside half and falls short of short leg. Some puff of dust there as the ball landed!
Quicker and fuller on middle, Moeen brings out the sweep shot and connects well to send it down to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller on off, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Digs in a short delivery wide outside off, Root hops and cuts it to deep point for a single.
Ishant switches to 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball around off, Moeen defends it from the crease to covers.
Ishant bends his back and bangs in a short one around off, Moeen leans back and sways away from the line.
Good length delivery in the region outside off, Moeen pushes it with gentle hands through point and takes a single.

FOUR! 150 for Joe Root! The crowd roars in delight. Short in length and outside off, Joe hangs on the back foot and plays a full-blooded cut shot. It flies past gully and screams away to the fence. The 50-run stand also comes up. England's deficit is now 28 runs.
Too full in length on off, Moeen knocks it down to mid on for a single.
Flatter and around off, Root moves back and works it behind square leg for a single.
Floated one, full and on off, Moeen defends it back with a straight blade.
Loopy and full, it lands on the rough outside off and spins back in, Moeen goes back and defends.
Spinning in from around off, Moeen uses the turn and works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Fires it full and on middle, Root uses his wrists and flicks it to mid-wicket.
A wayward bouncer, down the leg side, Moeen has an easy leave.
Action replay of the previous delivery. Waste of energy. Ishant is bending his back here but the line is letting him down. If you want to bowl a bouncer, target the head of the batsman.
Short and around middle and leg, angling down, Moeen ducks.
Back of a length around leg, Moeen glances it off his hips to fine leg and takes a single.
Good length ball around off, shaping in, Root tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the thigh pad. It then pops up to hit him on the stomach as well.
Wide outside off, on a length and holding its line, Root allows it through. The ball dies down on its way to Pant.
Fuller in length and on off, Moeen is forward with a straight bat in defense.
Gets on the front foot and pushes it to the off side.
Loopy and full on off, Moeen flicks it with the spin to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Tossed up ball landing full on middle, Root defends it to the leg side.
Flighted and on middle, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Slower one, full and on middle, spinning away a bit, Root draws forward and jams it down.
Misses the edge. Ishant lands it on a fuller length outside off, Moeen feels for it but it shapes away a bit to beat the outside edge.
Fuller length ball, drifting down the leg side, Ali tries to flick but misses. Pant dives across to his right and collects the ball.
A bouncer on middle, Moeen lets it go over him.
Moeen continues to play and miss. A length delivery outside off, holding its line, Moeen goes fishing for it and is beaten.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! This was on the cards with so many deliveries beating the edge. Ishant gets lucky on this occasion. He keeps probing with a length ball close to off and gets it to hold its line. Moeen has a tame push inside the line and edges it to first slip. Virat Kohli goes down low to snap it inches above the ground. He claims the catch and Moeen is ready to walk. Hang on, the umpires want to get it checked. They go upstairs and gives the soft signal as out. The replays come and show that Kohli's fingers are underneath the ball. Moeen can continue with his walk. The 58-run stand is broken and England trail by 23 runs.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Ishant Sharma

Commentary: OUT! Two in two for Ishant Sharma and India are making a comeback in the evening session. A golden duck for Curran and Ishant is on a hat-trick. He will have to wait though for his next over. Sharma dishes out a perfect delivery, on a length and close to off, Curran has to play the trajectory but the ball straightens from there to take the outside edge. It flies to Rohit Sharma at second slip and he is not going to drop those.
Howout: c Rohit Sharma b Ishant Sharma

Commentary: Loopy and full on off, defended off the front foot.
A touch short and on middle, Root goes on the back foot and defends it on the leg side.
Fuller and on middle, clipped softly to square leg for a run.
Flatter and shorter outside off, Ollie plays outside the line as he tries to cut and misses. Beats the inside edge.
Fires it flat and on off, it's defended from the back foot.
Tossed up ball landing full on middle, Ollie Robinson strides forward and defends it in front of his pads.
No hat-trick. Fuller in length and on middle, Root nudges it down to fine leg for a single.
Angles in a length ball on off, Robinson defends it back to the bowler.
Bouncer, well-directed, Ollie Robinson sways away from the line of fire at the last moment.
Edgy! Fuller in length and outside off, Ollie tries to drive but it takes the inner edge and goes past the stumps to square leg. They take a run.
Drifting down the leg side, fuller in length, Root flicks it through square leg and picks up a run.
Sliding down the leg side, Robinson eases it behind square leg for one. India won't mind Ollie on strike against Jadeja. Okay, that's given as a leg bye, so there was no bat involved.
Fuller and on off, defended off the front foot to silly point.
Too full and on off, Ollie digs it out to covers.
Full and floated on off, Robinson defends it back safely.
Quicker one, fires it full on middle, Ollie helps it to square leg for one.
Loopy and full on middle, Root gets forward and works it gently to square leg. Looks for a run but his partner says no.
Fires it in again, flat and a touch short, Joe moves back and helps it to square leg. Jadeja's over comes and goes without making you realize.
Back of a length, close to off, Robinson defends it from the back foot to the off side.

Shout for an lbw, not given. Seems too high. Good length ball landing on off, jagging back in, Robinson tries to defend but misses. He is pinged on the pads, the bowler appeals but to no avail. Siraj tries to convince his skipper, Kohli remains unmoved and then gives him a thumbs up. Not taking the DRS.
Ufff...this one stays very low. Around off, on a fuller length just outside off, Ollie pushes at it but misses. Pant does well to collect it.
FOUR! Slapped away! Short and wide outside off, Robinson hangs back and whacks it through point for a boundary.
Another shout for an lbw! Turned down. An inswinger from a length outside off, Ollie again fails to keep it out and is pinged on the pads. Too high, Kohli gestures the same.

Siraj is getting the ball to move in a mile. There is another big appeal for an lbw but it's not entertained. Ollie so far has not managed to get bat on any of the inswingers. Siraj tries to convince his skipper. Kohli has a big smile on his face but doesn't go for the DRS. The replays show that it was clipping the leg stump.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Full and floated on middle, Root defends it to the leg side.
FOUR! Smashed away! A slow low full toss on off, Root whips it across the line and finds the fence at mid-wicket. The deficit is under 10 now.
Flighted and on off, defended off the front foot.
Knocks a full ball down to mid on, finds the fielder.
Loopy and around off, Root drives it through the line to mid off and takes a single to retain strike.
Drifting down the leg side, Root tries to glance but misses. It clips his thigh pad and races past the diving keeper to fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Good length ball on off, Robinson defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Pitches it up and around off, Ollie digs it out to mid off.
Beats the outside edge! Back of a length, outside off and shaping away, Ollie feels for it and gets beaten.
Inswinger, on a good length around off, Ollie defends it off the inner half to the leg side.

OUT! It's clipping the leg stump, umpire's call and Robinson has to depart. Siraj has a wicket and at last, he has managed to convince umpire Michael Gough with his appeal. Fuller in length and on middle, pretty straightforward, Robinson fails to keep it out and is hit below the knee roll. The bowler turns in appeal and the finger goes up. Ollie decides to review but it's of no use. His stay in the middle is over. England still trail by 7 runs and Root is running out of partners.
Howout: lbw b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Loopy and full on off, Root defends it off his front foot.
Root is not looking to farm strike. He drives a full ball through covers and takes a single.
Quicker one, flat and full around off, Wood defends it to cover-point.
Flighted and on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fullish and on off, Wood drives through the line and it deflects off the silly point fielder to covers.
Quicker one, fuller and on off, Wood has his bat down in time as he defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, close to off, Root plays it down from the back foot to point. Turns down the single this time.
On a length around off, nipping in, Root tries to defend but it takes the inner half and rolls through square leg. Again the available single is not taken.
Slightly short and on off, Root goes on the back foot and plays it down to point.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and offers a straight bat in defense.
Very full and on off, Root whips it across the line but finds the short mid-wicket fielder.
Shortish and around off, Root dabs it down in front of gully. Dot to finish the over and Wood will be on strike.
Begins his new spell with a delivery down the leg side, Wood tries to flick but misses. It possibly clipped his thigh pad on its way to the keeper.
Fuller delivery outside off, Wood drives it through the line, a bit uppish but not carrying to the cover fielder.
Shami hits the yorker mark, close to off, Wood has his bat down in time to dig it out off the bottom edge.
Swing and a miss! An outswinger outside off, Mark tries to play an expansive drive but fails to connect.
A leg-stump half-volley, Wood flicks it over mid-wicket and places it nicely to get a couple of runs.
Well left! A length ball landing just outside off, a hint of inward movement, Wood covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Too full in length and on middle, Root works it down to fine leg and denies the single.

Huge cry for an lbw! Not given. Virat Kohli has a word with his keeper and then looks at his bowler. This time he goes for the DRS with 3 seconds left on the timer. Good length ball landing around off, shaping in, Root tries to defend with his pad and bat together. It seems that Joe is hit on the pad first, Siraj appeals but umpire Gough remains still. Time for the replays then. The Ball Tracker rolls in and shows that it's clipping the top of the middle stump. Umpire's call. India don't lose their review.
Angling into the batsman, on middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Pitched up and around off, driven off the front foot to mid off.
Full and on middle, Root flicks but finds the diving mid-wicket fielder.

Appeal for an lbw, the umpire shakes his head. Siraj has troubled all the batters with his inswingers. Another one landing outside off and jagging back in, Root tries to work it around but misses. He is hit on the pads, they appeal but the impact is outside off.
Good length ball on off, shaping in, Wood defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Back of a length and outside off, Wood stays back and taps it down to backward point.
Too full in length and outside off, Mark tries to drive it through the line but gets a bottom edge. It goes on a bounce past the gully fielder to third man. The batters take a run.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Root nudges it behind square leg and collects a single. So Joe is trusting Wood against Shami. England trail by 3 runs.
Shami goes short and delivers it on off, Wood pulls it in front of square leg and the ball races in the deep. No run is taken.
A length ball is angling in from around off, Wood defends it back by getting half-forward.
Fuller length ball on off, Root presents a straight bat and defends it towards mid on.
Around off on a length, Root plays it late and taps it down to point. Steps out for a run but then turns it down.
Fuller in length and on off, Root flicks it behind square leg and again denies the single.
Siraj serves it full and close to off, shaping in, Root presses forward and defends it back soundly.

FOUR! England lead by 2 runs! Fuller in length and on middle, Root flicks it firmly off his pads, beats the square leg fielder and fetches a boundary. The crowd realizes that England are ahead and claps.
On a length around off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Starts his spell with a fuller length ball on off, Wood defends it from the back foot.
Aims for a yorker on off, Wood meets it on the full as he digs it out to the off side.
Good length ball on off, Wood defends it off his back foot. No ball called for overstepping.
Full in length and outside off, Wood pushes it off his front foot to covers.
Bumrah bends his back to dig in a short ball, around off, Wood sways away. Another no ball from Bumrah.
Bumrah goes short and around off, Wood goes back and pulls. It takes the higher part of his bat and goes over mid-wicket. The batsmen take one.
On a good length and outside off, Root is on the front foot as he defends it to cover-point.
A length delivery outside off, Root drives it on the up but finds the cover fielder. Root is disappointed with himself.
Siraj's search for his fifth wicket continues. Delivers it full around off, Wood tries to work it around but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length and on middle, Wood closes the face of his bat and helps it to square leg for a single.

OUT! RUN OUT! Fuller in length and around middle, Root flicks it through square leg and wants two. He, then, realizes that Jadeja is attacking the ball in the deep and decides to stop his partner. Wood though is ball-watching and doesn't realize. Root is quick to drag his bat inside the line at the bowler's end and Wood will have to depart as the throw has come to the striker's end and Pant has taken the bails off. Virat Kohli wants the umpires to check who got out but it's quite clear that Wood will have to go. The replays back the same.
Howout: run out (Ravindra Jadeja / Rishabh Pant)

Commentary: Drifting down the leg side, Anderson tries to flick but misses. Pant fails to collect it cleanly with a dive and Root calls his partner across for a bye.
Pitches it up and around off, Root drives but finds the cover fielder.

FOUR! Not the desired result although it's a boundary. Full and on middle, angling down, Root flicks it with great timing through square leg for a boundary. India will have six balls to target Anderson.

What happened there? It's a sharp short delivery, Anderson has tried to fend it away and it has gone straight up to gully. Bumrah appeals, thinking it's off the bat. Anderson is checking his helmet. Jasprit Bumrah wants his skipper to review. We all are waiting. The Indian players are also waiting as it's a blow on the head and the physio comes out to perform the concussion test. The replay is shown finally and it shows that the ball had pinged Jimmy flush on the helmet.
Bumrah is showing no mercy. Digs in another short ball around leg, Anderson tries to fend it away again but misses. He takes a blow on his body this time.

In the air... falls safely! No short leg in place. Bumrah bangs it in short and on middle, rearing up off the surface, Anderson takes his eyes off the ball, tries to fend at it but misses. It takes the face of the bat, lobs up but falls in the vacant short leg region.
Another short ball near the rib cage, Anderson somehow plays it down behind towards the keeper. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Shortish and outside off, Anderson goes back and plays it down to point. He wants a run but Root sends him back. Poor chap will have to face more chin music!
A rip-roaring yorker, around off, Anderson digs it out from the bottom half of his bat. The ball hits his pads and rolls back. Anderson shows his skills as he kicks it out. Called a no ball again.
Short and on off, jumping onto the batsman, Anderson fends it off safely.
Short in length and outside off, the batsman is not interested in playing at that. Called a no ball again. Jimmy would not be liking it. This over is going on and on for him.
Bumrah spears it in, around middle, Anderson keeps it out at the last moment to fine leg. No run taken. Another no ball. This is poor from Bumrah.
A fast-paced low full toss on middle, Anderson pushes it out to covers. Finally, this long over comes to an end.
FOUR! Root has decided to play The Hundred in this Test match. A length ball on middle, Root jumps across the stumps and plays a reverse-batted scoop shot over the slip cordon.

FOUR! Time to cut loose! A length ball around off, angling in, Root heaves it across the line and sends it flying in front of square leg. Jadeja puts in a dive near the fence, probably gets some hand on it but fails to stop the boundary. That would have been a stunning catch.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Gets on the front foot and drives it through covers for a run. He moves to 179.
Siraj comes from 'round the wicket and delivers a length ball outside off, Anderson is way away from the line as he tries to defend. The ball nips away and goes to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off, Anderson feels for it and gets beaten. He survives. 4 minutes left on the clock. Can India pick the final wicket?
Good length delivery on middle, Root stays back and works it off his pads to mid-wicket.
Full in length and close to off, Root offers a dead bat as he defends it to the off side.
Full toss this time, on middle, Root flicks it to deep mid-wicket and is not taking the single.
Fuller in length and on middle, Root nudges it in front of square leg for a single. Anderson has two balls to survive the day's play.
Back of a length, on top of off, Anderson hangs on the back foot and pushes it towards backward point. Yet another no ball for overstepping.
Fractionally short and outside off, shaping in, Anderson pushes at it and misses.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! A wicket off the final ball and England are all out for 391. Shami gets close to the stumps with his line, serves it on a good length at 81 mph and the angle takes it into the left-hander. Anderson is on the back foot to defend it but misses and finds his stumps shattered. With that wicket, it's STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Howout: b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: India and Rahul are underway! Anderson probably was looking for some away movement, he starts it on the leg pole but no movement, it is worked through square leg for one.
Rohit is underway too! A little too straight once again from Anderson. Sharma works it through square leg and takes one more.
Gets his line right this time! Lands it around off and this one comes back in. Stays a touch low. Rahul plays it to covers.
Well left in the end! This one comes back in sharply from outside off, it is a back of a length ball. Rahul does well to take his gloves out of the way and let it go.
The wicket seems to have quickened up! This is again outside off and it comes back in. Zips through. Rahul plays inside the line and lets it go.
Really good 4 balls to end! The pitch actually seems a lot lively than yesterday. The last ball is on off, Rahul blocks.
Slips this one down the leg side. Rohit looks to flick but misses. Not the best of starts from Ollie.
Right on the money this time! Length and around off, this one holds its line. Sharma looks to defend but it goes off the outer half to point.
Another one down the leg side, Sharma looks to flick but misses again.
On a length and around off, this one comes back in. Sharma looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
That is a beauty! He was getting it in but this time gets the ball to move away. Length and on off, this one moves away. Rohit is beaten as he tries to block.
Now brings it back in but it is well wide outside off. Left alone. A maiden to begin with.
Good length and it comes back in from outside off, Rahul plays it nice and late to gully.
On a length again and around off, solid from Rahul as he blocks it on the off side.
A little too wide outside off, left alone.

Really well played in the end! Back of a length and on off, this one takes off after landing. Rahul looks to defend but does so by taking a hand off the handle. It hits the higher part of the bat and goes to gully. Good he took that one hand off the handle or it may have gone to the gully fielder for a catch.
Relentless stuff from Anderson so far! Just continues to bowl that nagging line. On off and on a length. Kept out.
Inside edge! Once again on a length and on off, gets it to come back in. Rahul looks to defend but gets an inside edge. An appeal but turned down. England bowlers have started well. Another maiden.

BEAUTY! Not a lot can be done about that delivery but hope it does not take the edge! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Rohit is beaten as he looks to block. Again we can see the good thing the Indian openers are doing is they are not pushing at the delivery.
This time it is a little too wide, left alone. Ollie Robinson has overstepped so it is a no ball.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Blocked.
Another leave as another one is bowled well outside off.
Another one on a length and around off, defended nicely.
TWO! Good shot! Fuller and outside off, Rohit pushes it through covers. It is not off the middle and hence, two.
FOUR! Really well timed! Fuller and on middle, Sharma shows the face of the bat. He once again just pushes it past the bowler and down to the long off fence. A good over for India.
Outside off, left alone.
Just outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
A bumper now, left alone with ease.
BEATEN! Another one on a length, it pitches and moves away. Rahul is beaten as he tries to block.
Soft hands! Back of a length and on off, Rahul plays it late and with soft hands, it goes off the outer half towards gully, where the fielder dives to his left and stops it.
On the pads, Rahul looks to flick but it goes off the thigh pad to the keeper. Half an appeal but nothing.
Full and on the pads, Sharma works it towards deep square leg and takes one.
Another bowler who has started a little too straight, on the pads again, Rahul now flicks it towards deep square leg for one.
This time Wood bowls it wide outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Timed beautifully. Just used the pace of the bowler. Angled into the pads, Sharma flicks, he just puts bat to ball and this races away through mid-wicket.
Misses out! Probably looked to hit it way too hard! Shorter and outside off, Sharma looks to slap it but it goes off the underedge to covers.
Back of a length and on middle, Sharma hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
Nicely played in the end! Length and just outside off, Rahul waits and then opens the face of the bat at very end, he guides it past point for two. India trail by only 10.
Outside off, the batter does not fiddle with it.
Yet another delivery which is not on the stumps. Left alone.

NOT OUT! That is clipping the leg pole! Umpire's call it is! England do not lose a review but that was close! This starts around off, it is fuller and comes back in. Rahul for once, plants his front foot way too across, he can't get it his front leg out of the way as he tries to flick. He misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal, Anderson is pleading but turned down. After a chat with Root and Buttler. Root reviews. Replays show that the on-field call will remain. That could have gone eitherway.
Extra bounce now! Outside off, Rahul lets it be. Buttler collects it around his head.
Now this one stays a touch low! Another one on a length and just outside off. Rahul looks to defend but is beaten due to the low bounce.
Fuller this time and on middle, Rohit creams it but to mid on.
Just outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Rohit probably misses out at one again! Fuller and on off, Sharma drives but does not beat mid off. That was there to be driven.
Shorter and on off, Rohit pushes it to covers.
Good length and on middle, Sharma plays it to mid on.
Yet again on a length and on middle, Sharma is solid in defense.
Just outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Slightly fuller and on off, Rahul pushes it to mid off.

Really well played in the end! On middle, this one holds its line. Rahul does well to play it with a straight bat. He could have easily tried to work it which could have been an issue but he plays it with a straight bat.
A quick run! On off, Rahul pushes it towards cover and takes one.
Another one on a length and around off, defended.
Left on length again, outside off, this one comes back in. Sharma shoulders arms to this one. It goes well over the off pole.
A bumper, it is ducked under.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Rahul is a goner! Mark Wood gets the wicket England wanted. KL has probably been India's best batter on this tour and he walks back even before the deficit has been erased. Lovely delivery, Wood steams in, goes wide of the crease, lands it on off and then gets it to shape away. Rahul looks to defend but does so inside the line, it kisses the edge and goes into the hands of Buttler. Wood is elated. He is really bowling well and deserved this wicket.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Mark Wood

Commentary: On middle, Pujara defends it onto the ground.
Sharp stuff! Wood is bowling with a lot of fire here! Short and on middle, that is quick! Pujara ducks under it. He is mixing it up really well.
Just outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Good leave to end a successful over for England! Outside off, comes back in. Not enough though to make the batter play.
Anderson serves it on a length, outside off. Sharma shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, on the pads. Sharma flicks it through mid-wicket. The batters pick up two quiet comfortably.
A length ball, around middle. Sharma stays back and flicks it through square leg for just a single this time.
Back-of-a-length ball, around off. The ball takes off after hitting the deck. Pujara is surprised by the extra bounce and he defends it late towards gully.
Good length ball, outside off. This one does not trouble Pujara at all. He leaves it without any hesitation.
Another good leave! Good length ball, outside off. This one jags in a bit. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms at it.
Good length ball, around off. Sharma stays back and defends it to the off side.

Does not time it well! A length ball, around off. The ball come in a bit from outside off. Sharma stays back and punches it through point, but does not find the gap. Haseeb Hameed stops it comfortably.

SIX! You cannot bowl to Rohit Sharma, where he likes it the most. A touch short and on off. Sharma rocks back and pulls this over the square leg fence for a maximum. He made that 90 mph look like a slower one. Also, the scores are level now.
A sharp bouncer this time. Sharma was tempted to hook it away. But in the end, he smartly ducks under it.
A full-length ball, on off. Sharma was ready for it and pushes it towards mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Joe Root's decision of getting Mark Wood early into the attack is paying off really well. Wood serves a short ball and Sharma could not resist himself. This one is down the leg side, Rohit is probably a little early in the pull. It goes more of the toe-end towards deep square leg. Moeen runs in, slides forward and takes a good catch. Wood is on cloud 9, what a spell he is bowling. India in deep trouble now. Rohit is quite disappointed, he is looking at the bottom of his bat as he walks off. Now it is going to be a real test for the Indian middle order. They have not done that great so far and for once, the Indian openers have fallen cheaply in this series.
Howout: c Moeen Ali b Mark Wood

Commentary: Good length ball, outside off. Pujara shoulders his arms.
A length ball, around off. The ball jags in a bit. Pujara looks to flick it away but does not find any good connection on it.

EDGY! This was close. On a length, around off. The ball moves away after pitching. Pujara has a poke at it, but with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the man at first slip, but it meets him on a bounce. Pujara needs to settle his nerves and do what he does best, defend.
A length ball, angled into the pads. Pujara stays back and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Another length delivery to follow. This one is on middle. Pujara stays inside the crease and defends it to the leg side.
A touch fuller this time, on off. Pujara blocks it solidly with a straight bat.
Good-length ball, outside off. Kohli leaves his first delivery and lets it go to the keeper.
On a length, outside off. The ball jags in after pitching, but without causing any trouble to the batsman. Kohli prods and shoulders his arms.
A length ball, around off. Kohli defends it out watchfully.
Outside off, left alone by Virat Kohli.

FOUR! CREAMED IT! Kohli is off the mark with a boundary. A full length ball, and on off. Kohli leans and drives it through extra cover. The ball races away to the boundary. This shot is so pleasing to your eyes that you can watch it million times.
On a length, around off. Kohli stays back and blocks it out.
A full-length ball, just outside off. Pujara plays it late and guides it towards gully.

FOUR LEG BYES! A freebie and India will not mind. A full length delivery, on the pads. Pujara looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and flies towards fine leg. It also beats the diving effort of Jos Buttler. The ball ends up in the boundary at fine leg. The umpire signals a leg bye.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Pujara ducks under it.
A touch short and around off. Pujara blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length, around the hips. Pujara stays back and clips it to square leg.
A length ball, on off. This one jags in a bit. Pujara defends it out watchfully.
A full-length ball, on off. Kohli defends it out watchfully.
Overpitched and just outside off. Kohli drives it through cover, but this time there is a fielder present in the deep. They only take a single.
A full length delivery, around off. The ball swing in a bit. Pujara defends it out with ease.
Good-length ball, outside off. Pujara shoulders his arms.
On a length, around off. Pujara blocks it to cover.
A full length delivery, on the pads. Pujara stays back and flicks it through mid-wicket.

FOUR! Another exclusive cover drive! Kohli is not holding back and rightly so. He knows India need to score runs too. Full and outside off, Kohli drives it through covers. The fielder at point hares after it, dives and tries to stop but fails to do so.
BEATEN! Do not think Kohli needed to play at that! Length and outside off, Kohli has a poke at it. Beaten.
Angled into the pads, Kohli works it through square leg for one.
Well played in the end! Good length and this one comes back in from outside off. Pujara does well to drop his hands and lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length and on middle, blocked.
On off, Pujara plays it towards point, he wants one but is sent back.
Another single! Outside off, Kohli guides it through point for one.
Pujara is yet to get off the mark! Length and on off, defended.
28 balls now! Angled in on off, Pujara blocks it solidly.
Outside off, Pujara lets it through to the keeper.
Gets it to shape back in well from outside off, Pujara takes his front leg out of the way and works it to mid-wicket.
Good from Moeen! Kept Pujara on 0! On middle, Pujara looks to play it with a straight bat, it goes off the inner half towards square leg. Moeen dives and stops it. Pressure is kept on Pujara.
Robinson serves a good length delivery, outside off. Kohli watches it carefully and shoulders his arms.
Another one outside off. This comes in on a length and shapes away a bit. Kohli has no interest in playing that one.
On a length, outside off. Kohli shoulders arms at it.
A full length delivery, just outside off. Kohli leaves it alone.
A full-length ball and on off. Kohli defends it out solidly.
On a length, around off. The ball jags in a bit. Kohli stays back and remains solid in his defense to keep this one out.
Curran comes 'round the wicket. He serves a full length ball, around off. Pujara defends it out watchfully.
Full and on middle. This is angled into the batter, Pujara hangs and defends it out.
Is this into the gap? NO! Pujara is yet to get off the mark. A full-length ball, outside off. Pujara pushes it through point but he does not find the gap. The pressure is still on.
Pujara gets off the mark! The crowd cheers him as he crosses. A full-length ball, on the pads. Pujara stays back and flicks it through square leg. This brings a smile on his face as well.
A fullish delivery, around off. Kohli pushes it to cover but straight to the man.
Curran continues to keep it full, but this time pitches it on middle. Kohli whips it to the right of mid on and takes off for a single.
FOUR! Played that one with soft hands! On a length, outside off. Kohli looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes past gully. The ball ends up in the boundary at third man.
A full-length ball, on off. Kohli defends it to cover.
Full and on off. Kohli defends it out solidly.
BEATEN! Robinson comes up with a beauty. On a length, outside off. The ball moves away after hitting the deck. Kohli looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.

FOUR! Nicely played. This is also the second boundary of the over. Quicker. Full and on middle. Kohli stays back and clips it past the short leg fielder. The ball races away to the boundary. Only if the man at short leg could watch that one is slow-motion, he could have grabbed it but it just went past him in a flash.
A length ball, outside off. Kohli shoulders his arms.
On a length, outside off, this one comes in. Pujara is not troubled by the movement and he shoulders his arms to it.
Full and on off. Pujara defends it out solidly.
A touch fuller and on off. Pujara defends it out to cover watchfully.
A full length ball, on off. Pujara gets it to backward point off the outer half of the blade and gets a single.
Full and on off. Kohli pushes it to cover.

NOT OUT!  England lose a review this time. Good-length ball, around leg. This one jags in.Kohli stays inside the crease and looks to flick it away but misses and gets rapped high on the pads. Sam Curran appeals for it but the umpire shakes his head. Curran is convinced that he has got the batter and Root decides to take it upstairs, maybe because it's Virat Kohli and he got optimistic about this one. The Ultra Edge shows no bat is involved. Hawk Eye confirms that the ball is missing the wickets. The on-field decision stands.
Nips back in! Length and around off, this one comes back in. Pujara looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, this time Pujara plays it back solidly to the bowler.
Slightly fuller and around off, Pujara pushes it to covers.
Just safe! Angled into middle, Pujara looks to play it with an angled bat, it goes off the inner half, uppishly past square leg for a run.
Goes fuller this time and on off, Kohli pushes it to mid off.
LEG BYE! A length ball, on the pads. Kohli looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and goes towards fine leg. The batters collect a leg bye.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Sam Curran brings out the Imran Tahir celebration as he runs around in joy! Why not? He has had a poor time so far in this Test, no wickets in the first innings, a duck that too a first ball duck with the bat but he has got the big fish, the Indian skipper who was looking solid, Virat Kohli. India are effectively 28 for 3. Once again Kohli did not need to play at that one. For the second time in this series he has fallen to a delivery which he could have easily left. It is on a length, it lands just outside off and angles away further. Maybe Kohli was worried about the ball coming back in or maybe he was just done in by the angle as Curran was constantly changing sides. Kohli has probably been sucked into the trap. He pushes at it, the ball goes off the outside edge and the keeper takes it. Kohli walks back shaking his head, he knows he has made a mistake. Still some time for Lunch, England would love another one. Also, this dismissal reminded me of how Sachin was dismissed 19 years ago to Pedro Collins. That same angle, the tall left-arm pacer, landed it around off and angled it away. Sachin poked at it, it found the edge and Jacobs did the rest. It was the third Test in 2002 between India and Windies in Bridgetown. India went onto lose that game by 10 wickets. They are in deep trouble here too.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Sam Curran

Commentary: Overpitched full and outside off. Rahane stays back and drives it to cover. Dominic Sibley does well to dive to his left and make the stop.
Full and on the pads. Rahane stays inside the crease and flicks it through square leg. Rahane gets off the mark with a single.
Curran serves it full and on middle. Pujara defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, on off. Pujara defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
A full-length ball, around off. Pujara defends it to the off side off the front foot.

CLOSE! Robinson steams in a length ball, around off. This one jags in a long way. Rahane is beaten in his defense and gets rapped on the pads. Robinson and company appeal for an LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Root asks a couple of questions to his team-mates and in the end goes against taking the review.
Fullish and on off. Rahane defends it out solidly.
Back-of-a-length ball, around off. Rahane defends it out awkwardly in the end.
Good-length ball, on off. Rahane defends it out solidly.
Length delivery, around off. Rahane continues to remain solid in his defense. He has to survive one last delivery before Lunch.
A full-length ball, on off. Rahane stays back and defends it out watchfully. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4. India have a lead of 29 runs but they surely do not many wickets left by their side.
Wood starts with a length ball, around off. Pujara defends it out solidly.
A full-length ball, on off. Pujara defends it out watchfully.
Keeps it at the stumps yet again. A length ball, around off. Coming back in. Pujara goes back and defends it with a straight bat.
A length ball, on the pads. Pujara stays inside the crease and flicks it towards square leg.
A full-length ball, just outside off. This one comes back in. Pujara defends it off the front foot.
Full and on middle. Pujara blocks it towards short mid on. A maiden for Wood.
On a length, around off. Rahane taps it to point. He ventures out looking for a run. but Pujara sends him back.
A good-length ball, outside off. Rahane shoulders his arms without any hesitation.
Back-of-a-length ball, around off. Rahane defends it to backward point.
On a length, outside off, moving away after pitching. Rahane let's it go to the keeper.
A full-length ball, on off. Rahane stays inside the crease and defends it to cover.
Good quick single. India get their first run after Lunch. A length ball, on off. Rahane defends it to point and takes off for a quick single.
A length ball, around off. This jags in. Rahane stays inside the crease and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
On a length, around off. Pujara hangs back and defends it to point.
Back-of-a-length ball, on middle. Pujara ducks under this one.
A length ball, on off. Rahane pushes it to cover and rotates the strike.
On a length, just outside off. Rahane looks to push it to cover. But only manages to get an underedge on it. The ball ends up on the pitch itself.
A full-length ball, on off. Rahane pushes it to the right of mid off. James Anderson dives to his right to make a great stop.
Tap and run! A length ball, on off. Pujara taps it to the off side and he is quick enough to reach the other side. A single then.
Good lenght ball, around off. Rahane gets an inside edge onto the pads. No trouble here, as it does not sneak past the stumps.
Fuller length ball, on off. Rahane defends it towards gully.

A length ball, on off. Rahane looks to defend it out, but he gets an inside edge onto the pads. There is a short leg fielder in place, but this one pops up to the off side. Root has a smile on his face after seeing this.
A length ball, on off. Rahane pushes it to cover but straight to the fielder.
Good leave! Good-length ball, outside off. Rahane comes across and shoulders his arms.
A length ball, on off. Pujara defends it to the leg side, off the inner half.
A length ball, on the pads. Pujara tucks it to the right of mid on.

EDGED BUT SHORT! A length ball, around off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Pujara has a poke at it, but with soft hand. The ball takes the outside edge and falls short of Jonny Bairstow at second slip.
On a length, around off. Pujara pushes it to cover and scamper through for a single.
Full and outside off. Rahane lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length, around off. Rahane defends it out watchfully.
Good length and on off, Pujara defends it right under his eyes.
Back of a length and on middle, Pujara drops one hand off the handle and defends.
Close! This lands just outside off, holds its line. Pujara initially looks to defend but right at the end, pulls his bat back. Well played.
Another one on a length and around off, defended.
Around off and on a length, Pujara guides it to point.
Angled into the middle pole, Pujara hangs back and plays it onto the ground. England giving nothing away. Just the 5 runs so far after the break.
Make that 6. Short and on middle, this is pulled wide of the fielder at mid on for one.
On off, Pujara blocks. The zip off the surface which we saw earlier on seems to have disappeared.
Angled into middle, Pujara works it through square leg for one.
Another one on off, Rahane defends.
Outer half! This is slightly fuller, comes back in from outside off. Rahane looks to play it with a straight bat but it goes more off the outer half to point.
A pacey bumper to end, Rahane ducks under it.
Solid again! On off, Pujara keeps it out. Not sure if this tactic is the right one, India are going nowhere playing like this.
Slightly fuller and around off, Pujara pushes it to mid off. Another dot.
Well bowled! Angled into the middle pole, Pujara works it to short leg.
Dealing in singles at the moment! Fuller and on off, Pujara pushes it towards mid off for one.
On middle, Rahan pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length and on middle, Rahane keeps it out. 33 overs done, the lead is 37.
Bowls one well wide outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Slightly shorter and around off, Pujara looks to cut but gets an underedge towards covers.
Well fielded! Shorter and on off, this time Pujara slaps it from closer to the middle, the fielder at covers dives to his left and parries it to point.
Better from Curran! Lands it on a length and on off, blocked.
Yet again on a length and on the off pole, it is kept out.
Outside off, Pujara leaves it alone. A maiden to begin with by Curran.
On middle, Rahane looks to defend but this goes more off the inner half towards square leg.
FOUR! Hammered away and that should release a little bit of pressure! Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for a boundary.
On middle, kept out.
Too high! Length and outside off, it comes back in. Rahane looks to leave it on length but gets hit high on the pdas.
On off, Rahane defends it nicely.
A harmless ball to end, quite wide outside off, left alone.
Angles it away from off, similar to what he bowled to Kohli. Pujara shows what Kohli should have done as he lets it go.
And again, Pujara walks across, covers his off pole and lets this one outside off go to the keeper.
BEATEN! That is a beauty! Length and it starts on middle, keeps moving away. Pujara is beaten as he tries to defend.
Slightly shorter than the last ball this time and on middle, blocked.
Two more! On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for a couple.
Shorter in length and on middle, Pujara pulls it through square leg for one.
Another one on the stumps, Pujara manages to keep it out again.
Angled into the pads, Pujara flicks but to square leg.
Continues to attack the stumps does Ollie! Blocked.
This one lands on off and then jags back in. Pujara looks to defend but this goes off the inner half towards square leg.
Just outside off, left alone.
On off, Pujara keeps it out right under his eyes. The ball is not doing a lot now, the help the bowlers had at the start has gone and batting seems easy.
On off, Rahane pushes it to the man at covers.  He wants a run but is sent back.

FOUR! A gift and the good thing is Rahane puts it away! England are hardly bowling any bad balls and it is easy to get away with the one bad ball you bowl here and there but Rahane does well to tuck it away. On the pads, he flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Slightly fuller this time, gets it to tail back in from outside off. Rahane pushes it to mid off.
Good length and on off, Rahane defends it out nicely.
Back of a length and on off, Rahane guides it to point.
Goes full again, not a lot of swing into the batter, this is pushed to mid off.
On middle, Pujara keeps it out well.
Really good fielding and this keeps the pressure on! Shorter and on off, Pujara pushes it towards cover. Anderson dives to his right and stops it nicely.
Angled down the leg side, Pujara lets it be.
Slightly shorter in length and angling into the body, Pujara nudges it towards square leg.
That is close! Pujara probably goes back to one he should be coming forward too. It is on off, he tough gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
A leave to end! Outside off, Pujara does not fiddle with it.
On middle, Rahane works it to mid-wicket.
Floats it up on middle, Rahane blocks.
Floats it up on off, Rahane lunges and keeps it out.
Slightly shorter in length, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On off, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Another single as Pujara nudges it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, outside off. The ball jags in after pitching. Pujara shoulders his arms.
On a length, around off. Pujara defends it out solidly. There are some cheers from the crowd, as this is the 100th ball that Pujara faced. That is some applause.
Back-of-a-length ball, outside off. The ball comes in after hitting the deck. Pujara sways away from the line of the delivery.
A bouncer now and on off. Pujara ducks under this one.
A short ball, going down the leg side. Pujara leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Pujara blocks it out solidly.
Looped up, on middle. A bit of turn this time. Rahane looks to defend it out but gets hit on the pads. Buttler and Root appeal starightaway but there is nothing from Ali. The umpire is also unmoved.
Flatter and short, outside off. Rahane pushes it to cover for a single.
Floated, on leg. Pujara tucks it to square leg.
On off, Pujara blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Pujara goes back and flicks it to the leg side.
Darted, on the pads. Pujara nudges it to the leg side.
SWING AND A MISS! A good-length ball, outside off. Rahane stays back and looks to cut it away but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Rahane stays back and punches it to cover. James Anderson there does well to stop it.
A length ball. This one comes back in from outside off. Rahane hangs back and pushes it to cover-point.
On a length, on middle. Rahane stays inside the crease and works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, just outside off. Pujara stays back and pushes it to cover. James Anderson this time dives to his left to make an half stop.
A very good yorker this time. On off. Pujara does well to dig it out to safety.
Floated and on off. Rahane pushes it to sweeper cover and rotates the strike.
On the pads. Pujara stays back and flicks it to square leg.
Flatter and on off. Pujara defends it to the off side.
Full and on off. Pujara skips down the track and defends it out.
Loopy ball, full and on off. Pujara clips it through square leg for a single.
Around off, Rahane defends it out watchfully.
A touch short, on middle. Pujara stays back and tucks it to the leg side.

Quicker. On a length and on the pads. Pujara flicks it past short leg comfortably, but could not get it past square leg. Dominic Sibley puts in a dive to his left and makes a brilliant stop. The pressure is on.
Back-of-a-length ball, on the pads. Pujara hops and defends it out.
FOUR! Finds the gap this time. A full-length ball, on the pads. Pujara stays inside the crease and clips it through square leg for a boundary.

Wood is consistenly going on the pads to get the short leg into the play but Pujara has done well to not put himself into trouble. A length ball, on the pads yet again. Pujara looks to flick it away but misses . The ball clips the pads and goes to the left of the keeper.
Wood comes from 'round the wicket now. A length ball, on the pads. Pujara blocks it out.
Massive spin for Moeen Ali. This means the pitch has slowed down. Tossed up and outside off. The ball turns in. Rahane looks to cut but due to the spin, it hits his glove and lands on the off side.

This one came in a long way. Even Rahane was surprised by it. Looped up, on the fifth stump line. The ball turns in off the pitch. Rahane looks to cut it away and manages to get some bat on it. If he wouldn't have, I can picture the ball going through to castle the stumps.
Short and outside off. Rahane cuts it to point for a single.
Flighted and on off. Pujara skips down the track and works this to mid on.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full and on off. Pujara defends it out solidly.
A short ball, on middle and leg. Rahane stays back and pulls it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Pujara ducks under it and leaves it alone.
A touch short, around off. Pujara defends it to silly point.

OUCH! That must've hurt. A short ball, on the bodyline. Pujara hops and looks to flick it away. The ball goes past the diving effort of Jos Buttler off the gloves of Pujara. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it off.
The England crowd is cheering as Wood proceeds to bowl. He goes short again, not a surprise at all. A short ball, and on off. Pujara manages to move away from the line.
A touch short, on middle. Pujara blocks it out solidly.
Short and on middle. rahane works it to the leg side.
Slower through the air. Full and on off. Rahane pushes it to cover for a single.
Full and on off. Pujara skips down the track and defend it out.
Floated full and on off. Pujara defends it out solidly.
On off, Short and outside off. Pujara stays back and cuts it towards point for a single.
On middle, Rahane works it towards mid on for another single.

TOP EDGE! A short ball, on the bodyline. Rahane hangs back and plays the hook shot. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards fine leg. Moeen Ali runs to his right and makes a stop near the ropes. The batters take a single.
A touch short, on middle. Pujara tucks it towards square leg for another single.
Back-of-a-length ball, on middle. Rahane ducks under it.
A short ball, on off. Rahane leaves it alone.
Back of a length and around the hips. Rahane tucks it to fine leg and rotates the strike.
A touch short, just outside off. Pujara works it towards point and gets a single.
Tossed up, way outside off. Ali is going for the rough patch way outside off. Pujara skips to the pitch of the ball and pushes it away with the pads.

A loud appeal for LBW but turned down. Loopy ball, outside off. This one turns in. Pujara looks to defend it but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Ali and company appeal but the umpire is not interested. Root has a chat with the bowler and decides to go against the review.
On middle, Pujara tucks it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Rahane blocks it out watchfully.
Short and wide outside off. Rahane stays back and cuts it through point for a single.
Full and on off. Pujara comes down the track and works it towards long on for another single.
A length ball, on off. Pujara defends it out solidly.

EDGY FOUR! A full-length ball, just outside off. Pujara looks to push it through cover. But the ball takes the outside edge and goes past the teh second slip. The ball ends up in the boundary at third man.

This one comes back in. Great stuff from Curran. A length ball which lands outside off. The ball nips in. Pujara looks to defend it out, but gets an inside edge and gets hit on his back leg. Curran appeals but the umpire is unmoved.
A length ball, on middle. Pujara stays back and defends it to the leg side.
A length ball, on the pads. Pujara defends it out.
On a length, outside off. Pujara pushes it to point.
Floated full and on off. Rahane defends it out.
Flatter and short, just outside off. Rahabe goes back and pushes it to point.
Flatter and on off. Rahane works it to mid on.
Slightly short and outside off. This one stays low after hitting the deck. Rahane looks to chase it but misses.
Around off. Rahane defends it out watchfully.
This was close! Short and outside off. Rahane continues to play on the back foot. He looks to cut it away but misses.
Back of a length and on the pads. Pujara flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
A low full toss and on off. Rahane works it through cover and takes off for a single. 50-run partnership is up between these two batters. They have done well to steady the ship for the visitors.
Back of a length and on leg. Pujara tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Pujara taps it out.
Back-of-a-length ball, around off. Pujara stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Curran ends the over with a slower one. A full-length ball, on the pads. The ball takes time to reach to Pujara. He clips it towards square leg. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one. First run of the session.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket and a single is taken.
Shorter and outside off, Rahan guides it to the man at point.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahane strokes it to mid on.
Gives it a lot of flight and lands it on off, Rahane looks to push it on the off side but it goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
A dot to end! On middle, Rahane plays it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on middle, Pujara keeps it out.
Good length and outside off, Pujara does not play at it.
Good length and on off, takes off after landing. Pujara plays it well with soft hands.
Angled into the pads, Pujara works it through square leg for one.
Good length again and outside off, left alone.
Another one on a length and around off, Rahane pushes it towards point. He wants one but is sent back.
Flatter and on off, Pujara pushes it to mid off.
Steps out but the length is shortened. Pujara looks to defend but it hits the pad.
Fuller, this is worked to mid-wicket.
A single now as this is flicked through mid-wicket.
On the stumps, blocked.

FOUR! Rahane would have had his heart in his mouth for a second. Really risky. Comes down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball, he tries to lift it over long on but due to the turn, it goes more off the inner half and wide of long on for a boundary.
A good-length ball, outside off. The ball stays low after hitting the deck. Pujara shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! CUT AWAY! On a length, outside off. Pujara stays back and cuts it through point for a boundary. This is the second boundary which comes post the Tea session.
Angled in on middle. Pujara defends it to the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Pujara lets it go to the keeper.
A full-length ball, on off. Pujara defends it out watchfully.
Just a boundary off the over! A length ball, around off. Pujara stays inside the crease and defends it onto the pitch.
On middle, Rahane works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on off, Rahane hangs back and pushes it to covers.
Steps out and pushes it to the man at mid off.
On middle, Rahane defends it nicely.
Flatter and outside off, Rahane pushes it towards cover for one.
Shortish and outside off, Pujara looks to cut but gets an underedge on the off side.
On off and on a length Rahane pushes it to covers.
Another one on the stumps, Rahane defends again.
Another one on off, Rahane pushes it towards cover agian.
Solid! On off, Rahane pushes it to the man at mid off.
Another one on off, Rahane strokes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, Rahane clips it through square leg and takes one.

DROPPED! Tough chance but should have been taken! Bairstow who is generally a good fielder, is the culprit! Shorter and outside off, extra bounce on this one. Rahane looks to cut, this goes off the top edge to the right of Bairstow who dives but spills it. A single taken. Needed that to be taken, it is a tough period for the bowlers and the fielders need to given them proper support.
Shorter and outside off, Pujara looks to cut but misses.
On off, Pujara pushes it towards cover.
Floats it up on middle, Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on off, Pujara keeps it out.
On off, kept out.
On a length, just outside off. Rahane stays back and punches it off the back foot towards point.
A full-length ball, on off. Rahane defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Full and on the fourth stump line. Rahane hangs back and defends it to point watchfully.
On off, Rahane remains solid in his defense, as he blocks this one back to the bowler.

NOT OUT! England lose their second review. On a length, outside off. The ball nips away a bit off the pitch. Rahane stays back and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. Anderson and company appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Anderson says there was some noise, but Buttler thinks otherwise. In the end, Joe Root signals the"T" and takes it upstairs for caught behind. The Ultra Edge confirms there is not bat involved. Ajinkya Rahane survives, and another review goes in vain for England.
Good-length ball, outside off. Rahane leaves it alone.
Good length and on off, Pujara keeps it out.
Once again on a length, Pujara lunges and defends.
EDGED BUT SHORT! Good length again, it lands on off and then straightens. Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge, the fielder at widish second slip dives to his left and stops it.
Another one on middle, Pujara keeps it out.
On middle, Pujara hangs back and keeps it out.
Outside off, Pujara does not fiddle with it.
This is worked through square leg for one.
BEATEN! Anderson goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole, it lands and then moves away. Pujara is beaten as he tries to block.
Another one on middle, Pujara defends it nicely.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Pujara pushes it out.
A dot to end! Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads. Rahane stays back and tucks it square on the leg side.
A length ball, around middle. Rahane gets behind the line and defends it towards mid on off the inner half.
Overpitched and just outside off. Rahane stays inside the crease and pushes it to cover.
A length ball, around off. This one nips in a bit. Rahane gets an inside edge onto the pads. Curran puts in an appeal but the umpire thinks otherwise.
Length ball, on middle. Rahane clips it to the leg side.
Full and on off. Rahane works it to cover.
Flatter and short, outside off. Pujara stays back and pushes it to point for a single.
Looped up and on off. Rahane works it to mid on.
Full and on off. Rahane defends it out watchfully.
FOUR! SWEPT AWAY! Floated full and on middle. Rahane gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.

Darted full and on the pads. Rahane clips it through square leg. Mark Wood gives it a chase and keeps it down to three. But he ooverthrows and the batters get another single. So they run four in total.
On off, pushed to point for another single. A good over for India this one.
A length ball, on off. Rahane keeps it out without any trouble.
Full and on off. Rahane defends it to cover.
A full-length ball, outside off. Rahane punches it through covers. Haseeb Hameed gives it a chase and is successful in keeping it inside by putting in a dive near the ropes. The batters pick three.
On off, Pujara remains solid in his defense.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off. The ball straightens after hitting the deck. Pujara looks to defend it out but misses.

BEATEN AGAIN! This was a beauty from Sam Curran. On a length, outside off. Pujara looks to defend but misses. But there was some noise there because of which there was a loud cheer from the crowd as well as Jos Buttler behind the stumps. But then they realise that the umpire is unmoved. Root does not go for the review.
Full and on off. Rahane defends it out solidly.
Short, on off. Rahane defends it out.
Looped up, outside off. Rahane defends it out.
Flatter and short, outside off. Rahane pushes it towards point for a single.
Full and on off. Pujara clips it to mid-wicket.
Floated full and on off. Pujara skips down the track and gets the ball away with his pads.
On off, blocked.
Another one on middle, it is kept out.
Another one on middle, Rahane is solid in defense.
On off again, kept out again.

FOUR! Fifty for Rahane! A solid innings! He was under pressure, short of runs but has come good when his team needed him to. Needs to continue though, only half the job done. Gets there with a really good shot! On off, shorter, it is guided past point for a boundary.
On middle, defended nicely.
Tossed up, outside off. Pujara gets to the pitch off the ball and keeps it out.
Floated, on middle. Pujara goes back and nudges it to the leg side.
Full and on off. Pujara guides it uppsihly to cover.
Floated, around off. The ball turns in . Pujara comes down the track, the ball goes off the pad and goes past the keeper. Pujara is back inside the crease in no time.
On off, defended out.
Full and on off. Pujara pushes it to cover for a single.
A length ball, on middle. Pujara stays back and flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full and on middle. Rahane clips it through mid-wicket for a couple now.
A full-length ball, just outside off. Rahane drives it to cover but straight to the fielder.
Fullish delivery, on off. Rahane defends it out solidly.
Angled in, full and on the pads. Rahane tucks it to mid-wicket for a single. The runs keep ticking for India. The lead is 117 now.
On a length, outside off. Pujara shoulder arms to it.
Tossed up full and on off. Rahane defends it off his front foot.
On the pads. Rahane clips it through square leg. The batters pick three before the fielder cuts it off.
Floated, full and on off. Pujara defends it to the leg side off the inner half.
Full and outside off. Pujara skips down the track and looks to drill it away but misses. The ball takes the bottom end of the bat and goes to the left of Joe Root at slips. The batter cross.
On off, pushed to cover for another single.
On off, Pujara defends it out watchfully.
Floated and on off, Rahane pushes it to point and takes off for a single.
Outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.
Tossed up, outside off. Pujara defends it out with his front leg.
Full and on off. Pujara works it to mid on.
Outside off, Pujara again offer his pad to keep it out.
Full and on off. Pujara flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Angled into the middle pole, this is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Fifty-run stand up! Shorter in length and on the body, this is pulled through backward square leg for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! England have finally broken the stand! The grit of Pujara comes to an end! A complete snorter was needed to get rid of him and Wood provides it. This is a back of a length ball on off, this takes off from nowhere. Pujara looks to fend it but the ball gets big on him, it goes off the top of the bat and lobs to the man at second slip where Root takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Joe Root b Mark Wood

Commentary: Two! Pant is off the mark! Shorter in length, this is pulled through mid-wicket for a couple.
A single now, on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Floats it up on middle, defended.

Direct hit but Rahane seems to be in! They have taken it upstairs! NOT OUT! Rahane is in! On middle, Pant comes down the track and works it with soft hands towards mid on. They go for one and now try for the second. The thorw is at the bowler's end and it hits the stumps. They take it upstairs but Rahane is in.
Comes down the tracka again but Moeen sees that, he drags his length back, Pant pushes it to covers.

Three! On off, this pitches and spins away. Pant looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge down to third man. Wood runs after it, slides and pushes it back in. He hurts his shoulder in the process and looks in pain.
Another one on middle, Rahane defends it nicely.
Solidly defended again as Moeen tosses it up on off.
Another direct hit but Pant is well in! On off, this is pushed to covers. They take one.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On middle, Rahane defends it onto the ground.
Flatter and outside off, blocked again.
A single as this shortish ball is pushed towards cover.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On middle, it is played back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Flatter and outside off, Rahane goes back to defend, this goes on with the arm. He is beaten.
On middle again, it is kept out nicely.
Two now! On off, this is pushed through covers for two.
Flatter and on off, it is pushed to covers.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Rahane goes now and India in deep trouble! Moeen Ali gets his first! Rahane was beaten on a similar type of a delivery a few balls ago. Does not learn from the mistake. This is flatter and outside off, it goes on with the arm. Rahane looks to push at it, it goes off the outside edge and Buttler does the rest. Both the batters who were well-set fall in quick succession, India lead just by 140.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Moeen Ali

Commentary: Full and outside off. Pant defends it to the off side.
Floated full and outside off. Left alone by Pant.
Full and around off. Pant pushes it through cover for a single.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Jadeja works it towards point for a single. He is off the mark on his first delivery.
TWO BYES! Full and outside off. Pant looks to whip it away but misses. The ball turns away off the pitch and goes over Buttler towards third man. The batters collect two byes.
A single now as this is eased towards cover.
Very full and on off, Pant jams it out to covers.
Well outside off, left alone.
Skips down the track and then works it back to the bowler.
Angled into the pads, Pant works it on the leg side for one.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
Edgy run! This lands on middle and then spins away. Jadeja looks to defend but it goes more off the outer half towards short third man for one.
Jadeja drags this from well outside off, through square leg for one.
On middle, kept out.
On middle again, Pant keeps it out.
Well outside off, left alone.
On the stumps, Pant keeps it out.
On middle, kept out.

OUT! TIMBER! That is a beauty! A perfect delivery by an off spinner to a left-hander. The last batting pair has been breached and now the hosts are into the bowling all-rounders! This lands on middle and then spins away. Jadeja goes back and tries to block but this turns enough to go past the outside edge and hits the off pole.
Howout: b Moeen Ali

Commentary: Tosses it up on off, Sharma defends it out.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
Two more! This is lfatter and on off, Sharma hangs back and looks to defend, this goes off the outside edge down to third man for two. Lead is now 150.
Floats it up on off, Sharma keeps it out.
Another one on middle, it is defended nicely.
Fuller and on off, Pant plays it to covers.
Shorter and outside off, Pant slaps but to covers.
On off, Pant once again finds the man at covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Skips out and hits this down to long off for one.
On off, blocked.
Floated full and on off. Pant pushes it to cover.
Flighted, outside off. Pant stays back and punches it through cover for a single.
Floated, full and on middle. Sharma goes back and defends it out so late.
Full and around off. Sharma strides forward and defends it out.
Looped up, on the pads. Sharma defends it out watchfully.
Full and outside off. Sharma slashes it through point for a couple of runs. Well, the English players have decided to take the new ball on Day 5. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4.
Starts with a length ball around off, from 'round the wicket angle, Pant gets forward and defends it with gentle hands to cover-point. Seemed interested in a run but then returned.
Angling in, from a good length outside off, Pant stays back to defend it down.
Beaten this time! Jimmy hurls across an outswinger, on a fuller length just outside off, Pant pushes at it tentatively and gets beaten.
Anderson angles in a length ball on off, Pant walks forward and works it in the gap at mid-wicket for a run. Anderson has two balls to bowl at Ishant.
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, an outswinger, quite wide from the batsman and Ishant has an easy leave.
Safely negotiated. Fuller and around off, jagging back in sharply, Ishant tries to defend but is hit on the pads. Probably outside the line and too high as well. Only a stifled appeal.
Starts with a length ball, angling away from the batsman outside off, Pant covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Robinson gets close to the stumps and delivers it on a good length, Pant is forward in defense and it goes off the outer half through point. No run taken.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep cover-point, no run taken.
Beauty from Ollie! Lands it around middle and gets it to seam away, Pant tries to defend from the crease but is beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, on middle and off, Pant taps it down towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike. One ball for Ishant to survive.
Extra bounce this time, from a shortish length around off, Ishant uses his height and fends it off. The ball is aerial but away from short leg.
Fractionally short in length and just outside off, Pant goes back and punches it to deep point. No run taken.
Anderson attempts for an inswinger but the line starts from middle and it takes the ball down the leg side. Pant fails to flick and it goes off his pads to backward square leg.
Fuller in length on middle, Pant closes the face of his bat and pushes it out safely to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Here goes Rishabh Pant. It was just a matter of time. Jimmy delivers it on a length and outside off, Pant hurries down the track and hammers it through covers. That went like a tracer bullet.
Sliding down the leg side, Pant tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to backward square leg and they take a leg bye.
FOUR! Bonus runs from the bat of Ishant Sharma. Fuller in length and around off, Sharma drives it through cover-point and it runs down the slope to find the fence. India's lead is now 165 runs.
Back of a length, on middle and off, Pant defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Fine shot for a couple of runs, the desired result for India. Fuller in length and around leg, Pant flicks it in the gap at deep mid-wicket.

OUT! GONE! An excellent line from Ollie Robinson and he has reaped rich dividends. The bowler is ecstatic as the danger has been averted. It's on a good length close to off and nipping away off the seam, Pant could have looked to play it a lot straight but his bat comes down at an angle as he pokes inside the line. The ball takes a healthy outside edge and Buttler makes no mistake to his left. India lead by 167 runs.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Back of a length, Shami pushes at it and misses.
Extra bounce again, short and outside off, Shami goes on his toes and plays it down from the bottom half.
Angling down the leg side, Shami tries flicking but misses. Buttler makes a good stop as the ball was swinging a lot.
FOUR! All runs count from here. The Indian tail will go down swinging. Width outside off, Ishant throws his bat at it and the outside edge takes the ball flying over the slip cordon.
Shortish and around leg, angling down, Ishant walks across the stumps, trying to glance but misses.
Walks across the stumps with another attempted flick but fails to connect.
Extra lift, from a shorter length outside off, Sharma fends at it but it flies over his gloves.
Anderson goes fuller and outside off, Ishant jumps down the track to drive it through the line but fails to connect.
Very full and around off, almost a yorker, Ishant walks across and flicks it through mid-wicket for two.

FOUR! That's a good shot! He should take the lead as he is a better batter than Ishant. Full in length and outside off, Shami stands back and drives it on the up. It's aerial but in the gap at covers for a boundary.
Short in length and outside off, Shami bends his knee and then tries to pull but misses.
Back of a length, on middle and leg, Shami jumps and taps it down in front of square leg for one.
Play and a miss! Fullish and outside off, Ishant aims for a big heave but fails to connect.
Too full in length and just outside off, Ishant brings down an angled bat and places it wide of gully to third man. A single.
Angling in, on a length around off, Shami plays it with soft hands and works it through square leg for one. The lead is now 180.
Starts with a full length ball down the leg side, Shami tries to flick but misses.
Wood spears in a very full ball on middle and leg, angling down, Shami again fails to flick and it goes behind off his pads. A good stop by Buttler.

Huge appeal for a catch! Not given. Joe Root has a word with his fielders and bowler and decides not to review. Two gentle deliveries to warm up and a nasty short ball to follow. Well-directed, Shami takes his eyes off the ball as he tries to fend it away. The ball goes past his gloves, probably took his left shoulder and ballons to gully. Rory Burns catches it, they appeal but nothing from the umpire. The replays confirm that it was off the shoulder.
Short and on off, zipping off, Shami tries to play the upper cut but misses.

Wood has another fall, right on the injured shoulder. Angling in around off, slightly fuller, Shami drives it back and Wood takes a tumble in his followthrough to stop the ball. Sometimes when the adrenalin is rushing, you don't remember your injuries.
Around off, on a length, angling in, Shami whips it across the line but the mid on fielder makes a fine stop.
On a length and around off, Sharma opens the face of the bat and pushes it through point for a single.
A little short and on off, angling in, Shami closes the face of the bat and works it through mid-wicket. Takes another run, the lead is now 182.

OUT! Ishant is a sitting duck! A clever change in pace from Ollie Robinson. He lands it close to off on a length and gets it to move back into the batsman. Ishant is late in attempting to flick it away and is struck on the pads. The appeal is made and the umpire raises his finger. Ishant takes the DRS but it's of no use. Plumb. The lead for India is 182.
Howout: lbw b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Slower one again, full and around off, Bumrah gets his bat down on it somehow and hit it aerially. It's wide of mid on for a couple.
Goes for a big slog across the line but only manages to drag it off the inner half to mid on.
Edged but safe! Slower one, full land outside off, Jasprit Bumrah winds up for a mighty heave but gets an outside edge. It falls in front of the diving Buttler.
Back of a length, outside off. Shami guides it through backward point for a single.
Quick, short ball on middle. Bumrah takes his eyes off the ball and swings through thin air.
Length ball, on top of off stump. Bumrah makes room and looks to swipe across but fails to connect.

In the air...wide of the keeper! Wood digs in a well-directed bouncer, Bumrah is caught in a fix as he tries to pull. Gets into an awkward position as it clips his gloves and files behind. Buttler is anticipating it to his left, gets wrong-footed and the ball evades him. There is a straight third man in place, so only a run.
Length ball, coming in from around off. Shami looks to block off the back foot but the ball goes through the gate and just over the middle stump.
Wood ends the over with a fiery ball, just outside off. Shami dangles his bat at it but the ball goes agonisingly past the outside edge.
Up in the air, safe again. Short in length and on off, Bumrah pulls it to deep square leg and the ball falls in no man's land. A single is taken.
Good length ball on off, Shami defends it from the back foot and keeps it out off the outer edge.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep cover-point for a single.
Slower one, swinging in the air and landing outside off, Bumrah is very early with his attempted slog sweep and misses.
Hits straight to the stumps at the other end. Fuller in length and outside off, Bumrah drives it straight back but for no run as the ball deflects off the stumps to mid off.
Slower length ball on off, Bumrah forces it down to long on for a single. 7 runs added by the current pair and India's leading is inching close to 200, only 11 short.

FOUR! Pulled to deep point, yes, it has gone to the off side. Back of a length, around off, Bumrah shapes up for the pull shot but it takes a thick outside edge and runs away to the deep point fence. Virat Kohli is all fired up in the Indian balcony.
Short in length and outside off, slower in pace, Bumrah tries to swing his bat again but misses.
Digs in a short ball outside off, Bumrah allows it through.
Bang on the helmet! A well-directed bouncer, Bumrah fails to pull and it goes off the back of his helmet to third man. Shami wants a run but he is sent back.
Fullish and on off, Bumrah goes hard at it and inside edges it towards fine leg for a run.
Full toss on off, Shami knocks it down to mid on and looks for a run. He is sent back as the fielder misses his shy at the striker's end.
Bangs in a short ball on middle, Bumrah pulls it down off the top edge to fine leg for a single.
Shortish and on off, Shami somehow pushes it in the gap at covers for a run.
Slower and fuller on off, Bumrah gets forward and defends.
Too full in length and on middle, 81 mph, Bumrah forces it down to long on and takes a single.
Easy single. Fullish and around off, Shami works it easily through square leg for a run. The lead moves to 198.
Short and wide outside off, Bumrah has a lazy poke at it and misses.
Back of a length, around off, Shami goes back and pushes it through point for a single.
Pitches it up and around off, a spicy delivery, Jasprit Bumrah clears his front leg and pushes it down to mid on.
Short in length, around middle, Bumrah turns and pulls it down to fine leg for a run. LEAD IS NOW 200! The Indian spectators in the crowd applaud and Virat Kohli is also clapping.
Make it 201. Wood bangs in a short ball on off, jumping onto the batsman, Shami leans back and keeps it out through point for another run.
